name: Blur
text: Your hero can't take damage this turn.
flavorText: "What are you trying to tell me? That I can dodge axes?" "I’m trying to tell you that when you’re a Demon Hunter, you won’t have to."

name: Shadowhoof Slayer
text: Battlecry: Give your hero +1 Attack this turn.
flavorText: Was a humble Elven Archer before Sargeras got to him.

name: Crimson Sigil Runner
text: Outcast: Draw a card.
flavorText: He's not the fastest of the bunch, but he'll take a stab at it anyway.

name: Demon Companion
text: Summon a random Demon Companion.
flavorText: Owning a pet can be real hell at times.

name: Double Jump
text: Draw an Outcast card from your deck.
flavorText: The key to every speed run.

name: Trueaim Crescent
text: After your Hero attacks a minion, your minions attack it too.
flavorText: You could have just pointed.

name: Battlefiend
text: After your hero attacks, gain +1 Attack.
flavorText: Say what you like about my hatchet-headed hooligan, he’s my battle-friend.

name: Consume Magic
text: Silence an enemy minion. Outcast: Draw a card.
flavorText: Please be mindful when consuming raw or undercooked magic.

name: Mana Burn
text: Your opponent has 2 fewer Mana Crystals next turn.
flavorText: One way to ensure that they are not prepared.

name: Twin Slice
text: Give your hero +2 Attack this turn. Add 'Second Slice' to your hand.
flavorText: The slice so nice, it'll cut you twice.

name: Ur'zul Horror
text: Deathrattle: Add a 2/1 Lost Soul to your hand.
flavorText: You face face face face face Jaraxxus!

name: Felscream Blast
text: Lifesteal. Deal 1 damage to a minion and its neighbors.
flavorText: All the souls start running when they see the felscream truck.

name: Illidari Studies
text: Discover an Outcast card. Your next one costs (1) less.
flavorText: "Don't read texts and drive."

name: Throw Glaive
text: Deal 2 damage to a minion. If it dies, add a temporary copy of this to your hand.
flavorText: "No, no, I said SHOW me the glaive!"

name: Chaos Strike
text: Give your hero +2 Attack this turn. Draw a card.
flavorText: "What do we want?" "CHAOS!" "When do we want it?" "WHEN LEAST EXPECTED!"

name: Sightless Watcher
text: Battlecry: Look at 3 cards in your deck. Choose one to put on top.
flavorText: What he lacks in sight, he makes up for in sleight-of-tentacle tricks.

name: Furious Felfin
text: Battlecry: If your hero attacked this turn, gain +1 Attack and Rush.
flavorText: Signature moves include Eye Bream, Feast of Soles, and Metamorphofish.

name: Immolation Aura
text: Deal 1 damage to all minions twice.
flavorText: If you can't take the heat, stop standing in the fire.

name: Netherwalker
text: Battlecry: Discover a Demon.
flavorText: You got to Nethercrawl before you can Netherwalk.

name: Spectral Sight
text: Draw a card. Outcast: Draw another.
flavorText: "Pick a card, any card! Preferably the left- or right-most card."

name: Feast of Souls
text: Draw a card for each friendly minion that died this turn.
flavorText: Nothing fills you up like soul food!

name: Umberwing
text: Battlecry: Summon two 1/1 Felwings.
flavorText: Demon Hunters refer to these glaives as "the ol’ flappy-attackys."

name: Redeemed Pariah
text: After you play an Outcast card, gain +1/+1.
flavorText: "Look at this stick. Look at it!"

name: Aldrachi Warblades
text: Lifesteal
flavorText: The ancient Aldrachi were the greatest warriors in the universe. Imagine their power if they'd put the handle at the END of the blade.

name: Coordinated Strike
text: Summon three 1/1 Illidari with Rush.
flavorText: Undisputed champions of "Dancing with the Satyrs."

name: Satyr Overseer
text: After your hero attacks, summon a 2/2 Satyr.
flavorText: What he lacks in communication skills, he makes up for with highly responsive staffing allocations.

name: Soul Cleave
text: Lifesteal Deal 2 damage to two random enemy minions.
flavorText: The way to a demon's soul is through its stomach.

name: Ace Hunter Kreen
text: Your other characters are Immune while attacking.
flavorText: This grandmaster marksman loves winning tournaments and eating a bit of ice cream.

name: Magehunter
text: Rush Whenever this attacks a minion, Silence it.
flavorText: Hates waiting. Abhors chit chat. Fond of the color purple.

name: Blade Dance
text: Deal damage equal to your hero's Attack to 3 random enemy minions.
flavorText: The surest way to clear the dance floor.

name: Eye Beam
text: Lifesteal. Deal 3 damage to a minion. Outcast: This costs (1).
flavorText: Sometimes looks CAN kill.

name: Wrathscale Naga
text: After a friendly minion dies, deal 3 damage to a random enemy.
flavorText: If throwing glaives is what you crave; summon tokens and make 'em broken.

name: Acrobatics
text: Draw 2 cards. If you play both this turn, draw 2 more.
flavorText: He soars through the air with the greatest of fleas.

name: Dreadlord's Bite
text: Outcast: Deal 1 damage to all enemies.
flavorText: When it gets too dull, it's more of a nibble.

name: Felsteel Executioner
text: Corrupt: Become a weapon.
flavorText: "My mom said I could be anything I want."

name: Insatiable Felhound
text: Taunt Corrupt: Gain +1/+1 and Lifesteal.
flavorText: Back-to-back winner of the annual hot dog eating contest... and the judge-eating contest.

name: Line Hopper
text: Your Outcast cards cost (1) less.
flavorText: There are two things Demon Hunters know: hopping, and cutting.

name: Relentless Pursuit
text: Give your hero +4 Attack and Immune this turn.
flavorText: If you steal a Demon Hunter's corn dog, you'll get what's coming.

name: Stiltstepper
text: Battlecry: Draw a card. If you play it this turn, give your hero +4 Attack this turn.
flavorText: Circus school was tough, sometimes you had to step on people to make it to the top.

name: Ashtongue Battlelord
text: Taunt Lifesteal
flavorText: Demons have destroyed the lives of the Ashtongue draenei. Now he’s got a shoulder-axe to grind.

name: Kayn Sunfury
text: Charge All friendly attacks ignore Taunt.
flavorText: "Armor and heals may slow my zeal, but fel and glaives excite me!"

name: Glide
text: Shuffle your hand into your deck. Draw 4 cards. Outcast: Your opponent does the same.
flavorText: "Come with me, and you'll see, a whole new hand of possibly the same cards."

name: Marrowslicer
text: Battlecry: Shuffle 2 Soul Fragments into your deck.
flavorText: Perfect for killing the first boss in Icecrown Citadel.

name: Shardshatter Mystic
text: Battlecry: Destroy a Soul Fragment in your deck to deal 3 damage to all other minions.
flavorText: Enjoys a good soul-crushing defeat.

name: Star Student Stelina
text: Outcast: Look at 3 cards in your opponent's hand. Shuffle one of them into their deck.
flavorText: Cheating is just using your resources wisely.

name: Vilefiend Trainer
text: Outcast: Summon two 1/1 Demons.
flavorText: My Vilefiend Trainers give me a much better sprint than my Air Gul'dans.

name: Altruis the Outcast
text: After you play the left- or right-most card in your hand, deal 1 damage to all enemies.
flavorText: Altruis betrayed Illidan to forge his own way in Outland. With Blackjack. And Netherdrakes.

name: Illidari Felblade
text: Rush Outcast: Gain Immune this turn.
flavorText: A whirling dervish of demonic devastation.

name: Raging Felscreamer
text: Battlecry: The next Demon you play costs (2) less.
flavorText: Screaming loudly will not reduce the cost of non-demonic goods.

name: Soul Split
text: Choose a friendly Demon. Summon a copy of it.
flavorText: Spoiler: they're both the evil twin.

name: Felsaber
text: Can only attack if your hero attacked this turn.
flavorText: Some drivers rev their engines. This one growls all on its own.

name: Il'gynoth
text: Lifesteal Your Lifesteal damages the enemy hero instead of healing you.
flavorText: Well, that just sounds like damage with extra steps.

name: Renowned Performer
text: Rush Deathrattle: Summon two   1/1 Assistants with Taunt.
flavorText: Cutting the assistant in half is the easy part.

name: Chaos Nova
text: Deal 4 damage to all minions.
flavorText: Illin' Illidan laying down the damage, flinging out the chaos as far as he can manage.

name: Glaivebound Adept
text: Battlecry: If your hero attacked this turn, deal 4 damage.
flavorText: "Initiate, this is your glaive. Think of it as an extension of yourself... Did you just throw it?!"

name: Metamorphosis
text: Swap your Hero Power to "Deal 4 damage." After 2 uses, swap it back.
flavorText: As the humble caterpillar becomes a beautiful butterfly, so too does a demon hunter become a hideous mass of writhing destruction and unfettered chaos.

name: Blood Herald
text: Whenever a friendly minion dies while this is in your hand, gain +1/+1.
flavorText: "Red Blood, it gives you wings."

name: Soulshard Lapidary
text: Battlecry: Destroy a Soul Fragment in your deck to give your hero +5 Attack this turn.
flavorText: Also known as a soul sequincer.

name: Command the Illidari
text: Summon six 1/1 Illidari with Rush.
flavorText: Give me an R! Give me a U! Give me an S! Give me an H! You two, you’re exclamation points!

name: Wrathspike Brute
text: Taunt After this is attacked, deal 1 damage to all enemies.
flavorText: You scratch her back, her back scratches back.

name: Zai, the Incredible
text: Battlecry: Copy the left- and right-most cards in your hand.
flavorText: Following this act will be her younger brother, Frank the Mediocre.

name: Fel Summoner
text: Deathrattle: Summon a random Demon from your hand.
flavorText: All's well that ends fel when the fel summoner summons well.

name: Imprisoned Antaen
text: Dormant for 2 turns. When this awakens, deal 10 damage randomly split among all enemies.
flavorText: Can I get a pair of size XXXXXL manacles?

name: Skull of Gul'dan
text: Draw 3 cards. Outcast: Reduce their Cost by (3).
flavorText: A fellow of evil possessed, of most devious shadow. He hath turned on his kin a thousand times, and now, how abhorred in all imagination he is!

name: Warglaives of Azzinoth
text: After attacking a minion, your hero may attack again.
flavorText: The blades glow green from things unseen, dark dreams whirling in the felfire gleam.

name: Bladed Lady
text: Rush Costs (1) if your hero has 6 or more Attack.
flavorText: While you were busy learning magic, she studied the blade.

name: Priestess of Fury
text: At the end of your turn, deal 6 damage randomly split among all enemies.
flavorText: Furious that she only has six warglaives. The Sightless Watcher has eight! The fel is always greener on the other side.

name: Cycle of Hatred
text: Deal 3 damage to all minions. Summon a 3/3 Spirit for every minion killed.
flavorText: If you run 2 of these, would that make it the bi-cycle of hatred?

name: Fel Guardians
text: Summon three 1/2 Demons with Taunt. Costs (1) less whenever a friendly minion dies.
flavorText: What happened after the guardians tripped? They Fel.

name: Flamereaper
text: Also damages the minions next to whomever your hero attacks.
flavorText: Honestly it sows more flame than it reaps.

name: Expendable Performers
text: Summon seven 1/1 Illidari with Rush. If they all die this turn, summon seven more.
flavorText: When someone gets injured, it's considered performance art.

name: Inner Demon
text: Give your hero +8 Attack this turn.
flavorText: Critical component of any tragic backstory.

name: Coilfang Warlord
text: Rush Deathrattle: Summon a 5/9 Warlord with Taunt.
flavorText: Prepare for the staunch conch launch!

name: Hulking Overfiend
text: Rush. After this attacks and kills a minion, it may attack again.
flavorText: To hulk, perhaps, to fiend: ay, there's the rub.

name: Pit Commander
text: Taunt At the end of your turn, summon a Demon from your deck.
flavorText: "Pit! Do as I say!"

name: Ancient Void Hound
text: At the end of your turn, steal 1 Attack and Health from all enemy minions.
flavorText: What happened to my 1/1 Void Pup? And the glee club?!

name: Nethrandamus
text: Battlecry: Summon two random -Cost minions. (Upgrades each time a friendly minion dies!)
flavorText: Missed the big descent with the other dragons. But better late and nether!

name: Innervate
text: Gain 1 Mana Crystal this turn only.
flavorText: Some druids still have flashbacks from strangers yelling "Innervate me!!" at them.

name: Moonfire
text: Deal 1 damage.
flavorText: "Cast Moonfire, and never stop." - How to Be a Druid, Chapter 5, Section 3

name: Embiggen
text: Give all minions in your deck +2/+2. They cost (1) more (up to 10).
flavorText: Did you set it to "wumbo?"

name: Lightning Bloom
text: Gain 2 Mana Crystals this turn only. Overload: (2)
flavorText: Curiously, this plant never blooms in the same place twice.

name: Claw
text: Give your hero +2 Attack this turn. Gain 2 Armor.
flavorText: The claw decides who will stay and who will go.

name: Savagery
text: Deal damage equal to your hero's Attack to a minion.
flavorText: It is true that some druids are savage, but others still enjoy a quiet moment and a spot of tea.

name: Acornbearer
text: Deathrattle: Add two 1/1 Squirrels to your hand.
flavorText: You’d be nuts to mess with the squirrel squad.

name: Crystal Power
text: Choose One - Deal 2 damage to a minion; or Restore 5 Health.
flavorText: Often used as healing crystals, but also good for throwing at people.

name: Untapped Potential
text: Quest: End 4 turns with any unspent Mana. Reward: Ossirian Tear.
flavorText: The official term is "strategic laziness."

name: Worthy Expedition
text: Discover a Choose One card.
flavorText: This isn't where I parked my mount.

name: Secure the Deck
text: Sidequest: Attack twice with your hero. Reward: Add 3 'Claw' spells to your hand.
flavorText: "Tied it down, boss. I don't really know why you asked me to do that."

name: Strength in Numbers
text: Sidequest: Spend 10 Mana on minions. Reward: Summon a minion from your deck.
flavorText: One minion, two minions... tree minions!

name: Treenforcements
text: Choose One - Give a minion +2 Health and Taunt; or Summon a 2/2 Treant.
flavorText: Treemendous value!

name: Gibberling
text: Spellburst: Summon a Gibberling.
flavorText: "As a Linguistics student I have studied the Gibberlings. I have determined they are speaking Gibberish."

name: Nature Studies
text: Discover a spell. Your next one costs (1) less.
flavorText: "I have a first edition! Go ahead, count the rings."

name: Partner Assignment
text: Add a random 2-Cost and 3-Cost Beast to your hand.
flavorText: In every group assignment, someone does all the legwork.

name: Mark of the Wild
text: Give a minion Taunt and +2/+2. (+2 Attack/+2 Health)
flavorText: Not to be confused with Jim of the Wild.

name: Power of the Wild
text: Choose One - Give your minions +1/+1; or Summon a 3/2 Panther.
flavorText: Never look a panther in the eye. Or is it 'Always look a panther in the eye'? Well, it's one of those.

name: Wrath
text: Choose One - Deal 3 damage to a minion; or 1 damage and draw a card.
flavorText: The talk around the Ratchet Inn is that this card is too good and should be a Legendary.

name: Crystalsong Portal
text: Discover a Druid minion. If your hand has no minions, keep all 3.
flavorText: Experience the draw of the wild!

name: Dreamway Guardians
text: Summon two 1/2 Dryads with Lifesteal.
flavorText: They're a nightmare to deal with.

name: Keeper Stalladris
text: After you cast a Choose One spell, add copies of both choices to your hand.
flavorText: Keeps your choices handy.

name: Crystal Merchant
text: If you have any unspent Mana at the end of your turn, draw a card.
flavorText: I won't ask about your mana curve if you don't ask where I got these.

name: Breath of Dreams
text: Draw a card. If you're holding a Dragon, gain an empty Mana Crystal.
flavorText: Ysera has the worst morning breath.

name: Shrubadier
text: Battlecry: Summon a 2/2 Treant.
flavorText: Her shoots can kill.

name: Rising Winds
text: Twinspell Choose One - Draw a card; or Summon a 3/2 Eagle.
flavorText: Do not talk to me or my chick ever again.

name: Steel Beetle
text: Battlecry: If you're holding a spell that costs (5) or more, gain 5 Armor.
flavorText: Steel you can trust—fashioned from the husk of an over-sized creepy-crawly.

name: Ironbark
text: Give a minion +1/+3 and Taunt. Costs (0) if you have at least 7 Mana Crystals.
flavorText: "The important thing, son, is to protect your spores! I have spoken!"

name: Guess the Weight
text: Draw a card. Guess if your next card costs more or less to draw it.
flavorText: "And then at the last second, I'll shapeshift into cat form!"

name: Lunar Eclipse
text: Deal 3 damage to a minion. Your next spell this turn costs (2) less.
flavorText: When the Azeroth is between the Sun and the Moon.

name: Solar Eclipse
text: Your next spell this turn casts twice.
flavorText: When the Moon is between the Sun and the Azeroth.

name: Healing Touch
text: Restore 8 Health.
flavorText: 8 Health, no waiting.

name: Savage Roar
text: Give your characters +2 Attack this turn.
flavorText: What do they roar? Nobody can quite tell, but it sounds like "Elephant Macho Breeze". It's probably not that, though.

name: Wild Growth
text: Gain an empty Mana Crystal.
flavorText: Grow your own mana crystals with this Mana Crystal Growth Kit, only 39.99!

name: Mark of Nature
text: Choose One - Give a minion +4 Attack; or +4 Health and Taunt.
flavorText: Druids call it the "Mark of Nature." Everyone else calls it "needing a bath."

name: Blessing of the Ancients
text: Twinspell Give your minions +1/+1.
flavorText: Arguably the cutest blessing.

name: Lifeweaver
text: Whenever you restore Health, add a random Druid spell to your hand.
flavorText: Lifeweaving is all well and good until it's time to cut the thread.

name: BEEEES!!!
text: Choose a minion. Summon four 1/1 Bees that attack it.
flavorText: Right before CEEEES!!!

name: Archspore Msshi'fn
text: Taunt Deathrattle: Shuffle 'Msshi'fn Prime' into your deck.
flavorText: Brave leader of the Sporeggar. Guided by the philosophy that one should not mssh with matters that are not one's msshiness.

name: Bogbeam
text: Deal 3 damage to a minion. Costs (0) if you have at least 7 Mana Crystals.
flavorText: Some think the mysterious bright lights in the bog are alien invaders, others think they're just swamp gas. Turns out, it's just druids.

name: Fungal Fortunes
text: Draw 3 cards. Discard any minions drawn.
flavorText: Far superior to a beanstalk boondoggle.

name: Imprisoned Satyr
text: Dormant for 2 turns. When this awakens, reduce the Cost of a random minion in your hand by (5).
flavorText: "C'mon down to Illhoof's bargain bin! When the satyr's free, he'll lower your fee!"

name: Dreaming Drake
text: Taunt Corrupt: Gain +2/+2.
flavorText: Some dragons dream of conquering Azeroth, some just dream of being 5/6s.

name: Faire Arborist
text: Choose One - Draw a card; or Summon a 2/2 Treant. Corrupt: Do both.
flavorText: The bad apple never falls far from the treant.

name: Moontouched Amulet
text: Give your hero +4 Attack this turn. Corrupt: And gain 6 Armor.
flavorText: The Suntouched Amulet melted.

name: Swipe
text: Deal 4 damage to an enemy and 1 damage to all other enemies.
flavorText: When a bear rears back and extends his arms, he's about to Swipe! ... or hug.

name: Bite
text: Give your hero +4 Attack this turn. Gain 4 Armor.
flavorText: Chew your food!

name: Keeper of the Grove
text: Choose One - Deal 2 damage; or Silence a minion.
flavorText: These guys just show up and start Keeping your Groves without even asking.

name: Soul of the Forest
text: Give your minions "Deathrattle: Summon a 2/2 Treant."
flavorText: "Reforestation" is suddenly a terrifying word.

name: Garden Gnome
text: Battlecry: If you're holding a spell that costs (5) or more, summon two 2/2 Treants.
flavorText: "Greetings, my little shrubs... It's whittlin' time."

name: Germination
text: Summon a copy of a friendly minion. Give the copy Taunt.
flavorText: I regret asking how sporelings are made.

name: Overgrowth
text: Gain two empty Mana Crystals.
flavorText: Zangarmarsh: it's a fungal out there!

name: Groundskeeper
text: Taunt Battlecry: If you're holding a spell that costs (5) or more, restore 5 Health.
flavorText: It’s tricky for dryads to tend the garden without trampling the flowers.

name: Kiri, Chosen of Elune
text: Battlecry: Add a Solar Eclipse and Lunar Eclipse to your hand.
flavorText: Now, when the Sun is between the Moon and the Azeroth... that's when you've got a problem.

name: Druid of the Claw
text: Choose One - Transform into a 4/4 with Charge; or a 4/6 with Taunt.
flavorText: Cat or Bear? Cat or Bear?! I just cannot CHOOSE!

name: Force of Nature
text: Summon three 2/2 Treants.
flavorText: "I think I'll just nap under these trees. Wait... AAAAAHHH!" - Blinkfizz, the Unfortunate Gnome

name: Starfall
text: Choose One - Deal 5 damage to a minion; or 2 damage to all enemy minions.
flavorText: Is the sky falling? Yes. Yes it is.

name: Crystal Stag
text: Rush. Battlecry: If you've restored 5 Health this game, summon a copy of this. ( left!) (Ready!)
flavorText: Arrives alone, but usually leaves with a friend just like him.

name: Anubisath Defender
text: Taunt. Costs (0) if you've cast a spell that costs (5) or more this turn.
flavorText: Also comes running when he hears a can opener.

name: Elise the Enlightened
text: Battlecry: If your deck has no duplicates, duplicate your hand.
flavorText: From cartographer to combatant, Elise has taken the road less traveled—because no one else could find it on a map.

name: Oasis Surger
text: Rush Choose One - Gain +2/+2; or Summon a copy of this minion.
flavorText: Surge's up, dude!

name: Aeroponics
text: Draw 2 cards. Costs (2) less for each Treant you control.
flavorText: Good seeds can go far.

name: Glowfly Swarm
text: Summon a 2/2 Glowfly for each spell in your hand.
flavorText: Glowflies are distant relations to spelling bees.

name: Twilight Runner
text: Stealth Whenever this attacks, draw 2 cards.
flavorText: Every morning you find two dead cards at your doorstep.

name: Arbor Up
text: Summon two 2/2 Treants. Give your minions +2/+1.
flavorText: If you can’t outrun a tree, you really shouldn’t be here anyway.

name: Greybough
text: Taunt Deathrattle: Give a random friendly minion "Deathrattle: Summon Greybough."
flavorText: The best time to plant a tree was 20 years ago. The next best time is when you lose a minion.

name: Starfire
text: Deal 5 damage. Draw a card.
flavorText: Balance is important to druids. This card is perfectly balanced.

name: Nourish
text: Choose One - Gain 2 Mana Crystals; or Draw 3 cards.
flavorText: Druids take nourishment from many things: the power of nature, the songbird's chirp, a chocolate cake.

name: Hidden Oasis
text: Choose One - Summon a 6/6 Ancient with Taunt; or Restore 12 Health.
flavorText: Amazing that it's been hidden, given the twenty-foot treant splashing around in it.

name: Emerald Explorer
text: Taunt Battlecry: Discover a Dragon.
flavorText: Make it a double dragon!

name: Forest Warden Omu
text: Spellburst: Refresh your Mana Crystals.
flavorText: She wishes all things could grow and flourish at Scholomance. If only she knew…

name: Runic Carvings
text: Choose One - Summon four 2/2 Treant Totems; or Overload: (2) to summon them with Rush.
flavorText: "That totem was beautiful… and you runed it!"

name: Ancient of Lore
text: Choose One - Draw a card; or Restore 5 Health.
flavorText: Go ahead, carve your initials in him.

name: Ancient of War
text: Choose One - +5 Attack; or +5 Health and Taunt.
flavorText: Young Night Elves love to play "Who can get the Ancient of War to Uproot?" You lose if you get crushed to death.

name: Overflow
text: Restore 5 Health to all characters. Draw 5 cards.
flavorText: It's a high five followed by a low tide.

name: Goru the Mightree
text: Taunt Battlecry: For the rest of the game, your Treants have +1/+1.
flavorText: He's untreefeated.

name: Winged Guardian
text: Taunt, Reborn Can't be targeted by spells or Hero Powers.
flavorText: Take these broken wings, be reborn, and learn to fly again.

name: Marsh Hydra
text: Rush After this attacks, add a random 8-Cost minion to your hand.
flavorText: Three heads of marsh-mashing, bog-bashing, swamp-stomping fury!

name: Umbral Owl
text: Rush Costs (1) less for each spell you've cast this game.
flavorText: It sleeps with one eye open.

name: Ironbark Protector
text: Taunt
flavorText: I dare you to attack Darnassus.

name: Gift of the Wild
text: Give your minions +2/+2 and Taunt.
flavorText: The gift that keeps on living.

name: Lucentbark
text: Taunt Deathrattle: Go Dormant. Restore 5 Health to awaken this minion.
flavorText: Always feels refreshed after a little dirt nap.

name: The Forest's Aid
text: Twinspell Summon five 2/2 Treants.
flavorText: Delicious Forest’s Aid! Made from real forests.

name: Cenarion Ward
text: Gain 8 Armor. Summon a random 8-Cost minion.
flavorText: Don't ask about his right hand. He's still growing into it.

name: Cenarius
text: Choose One - Give your other minions +2/+2; or Summon two 2/2 Treants with Taunt.
flavorText: Yes, he's a demigod. No, he doesn't need to wear a shirt.

name: Ysera, Unleashed
text: Battlecry: Shuffle 7 Dream Portals into your deck. When drawn, summon a random Dragon.
flavorText: Releash the Dragon!

name: Ysiel Windsinger
text: Your spells cost (1).
flavorText: Reach down into your lungs. The wind that resides there is your greatest treasure. It provides the gift of song, which is free. *But not less than (1)

name: Fizzy Elemental
text: Rush Taunt
flavorText: Loved. Hated. Carbonated.

name: Survival of the Fittest
text: Give +4/+4 to all minions in your hand, deck, and battlefield.
flavorText: Sometimes the fittest is the one smart enough to not start a fight with seven 6/6 Treants.

name: Arcane Shot
text: Deal 2 damage.
flavorText: Magi conjured arcane arrows to sell to hunters, until hunters learned just enough magic to do it themselves. The resulting loss of jobs sent Stormwind into a minor recession.

name: Timber Wolf
text: Your other Beasts have +1 Attack.
flavorText: Other beasts totally dig hanging out with timber wolves.

name: Tracking
text: Look at the top 3 cards of your deck. Draw one and discard the others.
flavorText: For the person who just cannot decide what card to put into a deck!

name: Bestial Wrath
text: Give a friendly Beast +2 Attack and Immune this turn.
flavorText: The seething wrath is just beneath the surface. Beneath that is wild abandon, followed by slight annoyance.

name: Rapid Fire
text: Twinspell Deal 1 damage.
flavorText: Pew! Pew!

name: Shimmerfly
text: Deathrattle: Add a random Hunter spell to your hand.
flavorText: Plenty of buzz around this card.

name: Unseal the Vault
text: Quest: Summon 20 minions. Reward: Pharaoh's Warmask.
flavorText: "Huh... That's a nice card back."

name: Clear the Way
text: Sidequest: Summon 3 Rush minions. Reward: Summon a 4/4 Gryphon with Rush.
flavorText: The terrifying part is the gryphons' squeaky voices afterward.

name: Dwarven Sharpshooter
text: Your Hero Power can target minions.
flavorText: Scissors, knives, needles, you name it! He'll shoot it.

name: Toxic Reinforcements
text: Sidequest: Use your Hero Power three times. Reward: Summon three 1/1 Leper Gnomes.
flavorText: In the event of a sudden loss of cabin pressure, a slingshot will be deployed for convenient evacuation.

name: Helboar
text: Deathrattle: Give a random Beast in your hand +1/+1.
flavorText: Beasts love Helbacon Strips!

name: Adorable Infestation
text: Give a minion +1/+1. Summon a 1/1 Cub. Add a Cub to your hand.
flavorText: Some cards are strong by sheer power; others draw strength from love.

name: Carrion Studies
text: Discover a Deathrattle minion. Your next one costs (1) less.
flavorText: A good read but a little too much fluff.

name: Overwhelm
text: Deal 2 damage to a minion. Deal one more damage for each Beast you control.
flavorText: Scholomance student Brewfest prank gone terribly, terribly awry.

name: Wolpertinger
text: Battlecry: Summon a copy of this.
flavorText: Scholomance student Brewfest prank gone awry.

name: Mystery Winner
text: Battlecry: Discover a Secret.
flavorText: Yeah, but the mystery prize could be anything! Even a boat!

name: Hunter's Mark
text: Change a minion's Health to 1.
flavorText: Never play 'Hide and Go Seek' with a Hunter.

name: Explosive Trap
text: Secret: When your hero is attacked, deal 2 damage to all enemies.
flavorText: It traps your food AND cooks it for you!

name: Flare
text: All minions lose Stealth. Destroy all enemy Secrets. Draw a card.
flavorText: Not only does it reveal your enemies, but it's also great for parties!

name: Freezing Trap
text: Secret: When an enemy minion attacks, return it to its owner's hand. It costs (2) more.
flavorText: "Dang, that's cold." - appropriate response to Freezing Trap, or a mean joke.

name: Misdirection
text: Secret: When an enemy attacks your hero, instead it attacks another random character.
flavorText: Sometimes it's as simple as putting on a fake mustache and pointing at someone else.

name: Scavenging Hyena
text: Whenever a friendly Beast dies, gain +2/+1.
flavorText: Hyenas prefer the bones of kodos or windserpents, but they'll eat pretty much anything. Even Brussels sprouts.

name: Snake Trap
text: Secret: When one of your minions is attacked, summon three 1/1 Snakes.
flavorText: Why did it have to be snakes?

name: Snipe
text: Secret: After your opponent plays a minion, deal 4 damage to it.
flavorText: A great sniper hits the spot. Just like a delicious flank of boar. Mmmmm.

name: Pressure Plate
text: Secret: After your opponent casts a spell, destroy a random enemy minion.
flavorText: The appropriate dishware for stressful situations.

name: Corrosive Breath
text: Deal 3 damage to a minion. If you're holding a Dragon, it also hits the enemy hero.
flavorText: It's a breath of fresh terror!

name: Phase Stalker
text: After you use your Hero Power, cast a Secret from your deck.
flavorText: It's not just a phase! I don't have to tell you anything! GAWSH!

name: Fresh Scent
text: Twinspell Give a Beast +2/+2.
flavorText: *Sniff, sniff* Elite troops... *sniff, sniff* ...armed to the teeth and... *sniff, sniff* ...BAAACON!

name: Imprisoned Felmaw
text: Dormant for 2 turns. When this awakens,   attack a random enemy.
flavorText: It doesn't care who woke it up, someone's getting bitten.

name: Pack Tactics
text: Secret: When a friendly minion is attacked, summon a 3/3 copy.
flavorText: "Just you wait, I’ll go get on my main!"

name: Scavenger's Ingenuity
text: Draw a Beast. Give it +2/+2.
flavorText: "A beast, barely alive. Gentlemen, we can rebuild it! Make it stronger, faster... spikier."

name: Bola Shot
text: Deal 1 damage to a minion and 2 damage to its neighbors.
flavorText: On second thought, bolas aren't very good against flying worms.

name: Dancing Cobra
text: Corrupt: Gain Poisonous.
flavorText: Snakes are just tentacles with fangs.

name: Don't Feed the Animals
text: Give all Beasts in your hand +1/+1. Corrupt: Give them +2/+2 instead.
flavorText: They're still cleaning up the mess from the last time someone fed the basilisk a deep fried candybar.

name: Open the Cages
text: Secret: When your turn starts, if you control two minions, summon an Animal Companion.
flavorText: "Coming out of my cage, and I'm dead by turn nine..."

name: Animal Companion
text: Summon a random Beast Companion.
flavorText: You could summon Misha, Leokk, or Huffer! Huffer is more trouble than he's worth.

name: Kill Command
text: Deal 3 damage. If you control a Beast, deal 5 damage instead.
flavorText: "Kill!", he commanded.

name: Deadly Shot
text: Destroy a random enemy minion.
flavorText: Our ballista operator is effective, but not picky.

name: Eaglehorn Bow
text: Whenever a friendly Secret is revealed, gain +1 Durability.
flavorText: First Lesson: Put the pointy end in the other guy.

name: Unleash the Hounds
text: For each enemy minion, summon a 1/1 Hound with Charge.
flavorText: You must read the name of this card out loud each time you play it.

name: Nine Lives
text: Discover a friendly Deathrattle minion that died this game. Also trigger its Deathrattle.
flavorText: Beware the night of the living pets!

name: Ursatron
text: Deathrattle: Draw a Mech from your deck.
flavorText: It's been programmed to include all the bear necessities.

name: Desert Spear
text: After your hero attacks, summon a 1/1 Locust with Rush.
flavorText: Goes on the right, next to the desert spoon.

name: Hunter's Pack
text: Add a random Hunter Beast, Secret, and weapon to your hand.
flavorText: Oh look! It's a trap!

name: Ramkahen Wildtamer
text: Battlecry: Copy a random Beast in your hand.
flavorText: She gets to decide what cards go to the Hall of Fame.

name: Diving Gryphon
text: Rush Battlecry: Draw a Rush minion from your deck.
flavorText: Warning: May cause carousel flashbacks.

name: Primordial Explorer
text: Poisonous Battlecry: Discover a Dragon.
flavorText: "We're letting the poisonous dude carry the bags?"

name: Stormhammer
text: Doesn't lose Durability while you control a Dragon.
flavorText: It brings the storm before the calm.

name: Chopshop Copter
text: After a friendly Mech dies, add a random Mech to your hand.
flavorText: Invention is the mother of entropy.

name: Augmented Porcupine
text: Deathrattle: Deal this minion's Attack damage randomly split among all enemies.
flavorText: Pokey-man. Gotta spike 'em all!

name: Zixor, Apex Predator
text: Rush Deathrattle: Shuffle 'Zixor Prime' into your deck.
flavorText: A living terror. Teleports at will. Feasts on tainted helboar meat. No head scritches unless you're Leoroxx.

name: Bloated Python
text: Deathrattle: Summon a 4/4 Hapless Handler.
flavorText: This is why Scholomance engineering students prefer C++.

name: Professor Slate
text: Your spells are Poisonous.
flavorText: "Don’t worry, this will be over in a second. It might FEEL like an eternity, but I assure you, it’s quite quick!"

name: Shan'do Wildclaw
text: Choose One - Give Beasts in your deck +1/+1; or Transform into a copy of a friendly Beast.
flavorText: She holds both an academic post and a scratching post.

name: Petting Zoo
text: Summon a 3/3 Strider. Repeat for each Secret you control.
flavorText: Welcome to the petting zoo. DO NOT TOUCH THE ANIMALS.

name: Saddlemaster
text: After you play a Beast, add a random Beast to your hand.
flavorText: Seat covers. Check. Racing stripes. Check. Cupholder. Check.

name: Houndmaster
text: Battlecry: Give a friendly Beast +2/+2 and Taunt.
flavorText: "Who let the dogs out?" he asks. It's rhetorical.

name: Multi-Shot
text: Deal 3 damage to two random enemy minions.
flavorText: You see, it's all about throughput.

name: Arcane Fletcher
text: Whenever you play a 1-Cost minion, draw a spell from your deck.
flavorText: Stop trying to make fletch happen. It's not going to happen.

name: Marked Shot
text: Deal 4 damage to a minion. Discover a spell.
flavorText: Obviously it's marked for greatness.

name: Hyena Alpha
text: Battlecry: If you control a Secret, summon two 2/2 Hyenas.
flavorText: Everything the sun touches is ours—so long as it's already dead.

name: Dragonbane
text: After you use your Hero Power, deal 5 damage to a random enemy.
flavorText: *Thunk* "That wasn’t a dragon!" *Thunk* "THAT wasn’t a dragon!"

name: Mok'Nathal Lion
text: Rush. Battlecry: Choose a friendly minion. Gain a copy of its Deathrattle.
flavorText: Never underestimate a lioness when her pride is on the line.

name: Scrap Shot
text: Deal 3 damage. Give a random Beast in your hand +3/+3.
flavorText: Make your foe's armor your fauna's fashion!

name: Krolusk Barkstripper
text: Spellburst: Destroy a random enemy minion.
flavorText: My friend went krolusk tipping once… once!

name: Rinling's Rifle
text: After your hero attacks, Discover a Secret and cast it.
flavorText: This rifle needs a muzzle for its muzzle.

name: Starving Buzzard
text: Whenever you summon a Beast, draw a card.
flavorText: If you feed him, he loses his whole identity.

name: Tundra Rhino
text: Your Beasts have Charge.
flavorText: Tundra rhinos are often mistaken for kodos. Or am I mistaken?

name: Explosive Shot
text: Deal 5 damage to a minion and 2 damage to adjacent ones.
flavorText: Pull the pin, count to 5, then shoot. Then duck.

name: Hunting Party
text: Copy all Beasts in your hand.
flavorText: Not sure I’d call it a good party if everyone ends up beside themselves.

name: Rotnest Drake
text: Battlecry: If you're holding a Dragon, destroy a random enemy minion.
flavorText: Clean your room, or I'm taking your favorite minion away!

name: Teacher's Pet
text: Taunt Deathrattle: Summon a random 3-Cost Beast.
flavorText: Really goes the extra mile to get the Hay+.

name: Trampling Rhino
text: Rush. After this attacks and kills a minion, excess damage hits the enemy hero.
flavorText: "Whew. I thought you said 'Trampoline Rhino.' Now that would have been scary."

name: Savannah Highmane
text: Deathrattle: Summon two 2/2 Hyenas.
flavorText: In the jungle, the mighty jungle, the lion gets slowly consumed by hyenas.

name: Oblivitron
text: Deathrattle: Summon a Mech from your hand and trigger its Deathrattle.
flavorText: Reduce, reuse, re-rattle!

name: Unleash the Beast
text: Twinspell Summon a 5/5 Wyvern with Rush.
flavorText: The Kirin Tor have always been lax in enforcing leash laws.

name: Scarlet Webweaver
text: Battlecry: Reduce the Cost of a random Beast in your hand by (5).
flavorText: Isn't that nice? The spider made the explorer a sleeping bag!

name: Swarm of Locusts
text: Summon seven 1/1 Locusts with Rush.
flavorText: Good things never come in swarms.

name: Wild Bloodstinger
text: Battlecry: Summon a minion from your opponent's hand. Attack it.
flavorText: Tame Bloodstingers would politely invite your minion to tea.

name: Veranus
text: Battlecry: Change the Health of all enemy minions to 1.
flavorText: As an empty nester, she just misses her little ones.

name: Maxima Blastenheimer
text: Battlecry: Summon a minion from your deck. It attacks the enemy hero, then dies.
flavorText: Believe it or not, this is only the faire's fourth most dangerous game.

name: Gladiator's Longbow
text: Your hero is Immune while attacking.
flavorText: The longbow allows shots to be fired from farther away and is useful for firing on particularly odorous targets.

name: Vereesa Windrunner
text: Battlecry: Equip Thori'dal, the Stars' Fury.
flavorText: Good things come in threes: Windrunner sisters and arrows of Thori'dal.

name: Darkmoon Tonk
text: Deathrattle: Fire four missiles at random enemies that deal 2 damage each.
flavorText: "Ready to roll out!"

name: Dinotamer Brann
text: Battlecry: If your deck has no duplicates, summon King Krush.
flavorText: Brann's new dino-taming hobby is going well—his pet can already make him sit, stand, and roll over!

name: Beastmaster Leoroxx
text: Battlecry: Summon 3 Beasts from your hand.
flavorText: Father of Rexxar, Champion of the Horde, and Flexxar, Champion of the Gym.

name: Guardian Animals
text: Summon two Beasts that cost (5) or less from your deck. Give them Rush.
flavorText: The guidelines specifically state: "Students may also bring an ironbeak owl OR an alleycat OR a toad." They never said how big.

name: Jewel of N'Zoth
text: Summon three friendly Deathrattle minions that died this game.
flavorText: This coveted gem calls for you to free it… and unleash an inescapable prison.

name: King Krush
text: Charge
flavorText: The best defense against King Krush is to have someone you don’t like standing in front of you.

name: Nagrand Slam
text: Summon four 3/5 Clefthoofs that attack random enemies.
flavorText: Come on and slam, and welcome to Nagrand!

name: Arcane Missiles
text: Deal 3 damage randomly split among all enemies.
flavorText: You'd think you'd be able to control your missiles a little better since you're a powerful mage and all.

name: Mirror Image
text: Summon two 0/2 minions with Taunt.
flavorText: Oh hey it's Mirror Image! !egamI rorriM s'ti yeh hO

name: Tome of Intellect
text: Add a random Mage spell to your hand.
flavorText: Just a compilation of napkins of intellect.

name: Magic Trick
text: Discover a spell that costs (3) or less.
flavorText: The world is not ready for an illusion of this depth and intricacy!

name: Ray of Frost
text: Twinspell Freeze a minion. If it's already Frozen, deal 2 damage to it.
flavorText: If you have zero chill, this can help.

name: Raid the Sky Temple
text: Quest: Cast 10 spells. Reward: Ascendant Scroll.
flavorText: "Why can't I hold all these scrolls?"

name: Arcane Breath
text: Deal 2 damage to a minion. If you're holding a Dragon, Discover a spell.
flavorText: One of many side effects from eating mana cookies.

name: Elemental Allies
text: Sidequest: Play an Elemental 2 turns in a row. Reward: Draw 3 spells from your deck.
flavorText: Reno’s lucky he wasn’t caught by a fire elemental.

name: Learn Draconic
text: Sidequest: Spend 8 Mana on spells. Reward: Summon a 6/6 Dragon.
flavorText: Upon taking up the spellbook, Reno realized with a start: "I can't read."

name: Violet Spellwing
text: Deathrattle: Add an 'Arcane Missiles' spell to your hand.
flavorText: A bird in the hand is worth three missiles in the grave.

name: Font of Power
text: Discover a Mage minion. If your deck has no minions, keep all 3.
flavorText: It's Comic Sans.

name: Lab Partner
text: Spell Damage +1
flavorText: "Professor, a gnome burned my homework!"

name: Glacier Racer
text: Spellburst: Deal 3 damage to all Frozen enemies.
flavorText: It’s just not the same without a super suit.

name: Arcane Explosion
text: Deal 1 damage to all enemy minions.
flavorText: This spell is much better than Arcane Implosion.

name: Frostbolt
text: Deal 3 damage to a character and Freeze it.
flavorText: It is customary to yell "Chill out!" or "Freeze!" or "Ice ice, baby!" when you play this card.

name: Icicle
text: Deal 2 damage to a minion. If it's Frozen, draw a card.
flavorText: This may appear weak at frost glance, but it's actually a very ice spell.

name: Mana Wyrm
text: Whenever you cast a spell, gain +1 Attack.
flavorText: These wyrms feed on arcane energies, and while they are generally considered a nuisance rather than a real threat, you really shouldn't leave them alone with a bucket of mana.

name: Sorcerer's Apprentice
text: Your spells cost (1) less.
flavorText: Apprentices are great for bossing around. "Conjure me some mana buns! And a coffee! Make that a mana coffee!"

name: Khadgar
text: Your cards that summon minions summon twice as many.
flavorText: "What do you call two minions summoned at once? Twinions, haha! Wait... where are you going?"

name: Magic Dart Frog
text: After you cast a spell, deal 1 damage to a random enemy minion.
flavorText: There's a powerful throat in this frog.

name: Mana Cyclone
text: Battlecry: For each spell you've cast this turn, add a random Mage spell to your hand.
flavorText: It'll put a good spin on your spells.

name: Ancient Mysteries
text: Draw a Secret from your deck. It costs (0).
flavorText: I'm not saying it was aliens, but it was TOTALLY aliens!

name: Arcane Flakmage
text: After you play a Secret, deal 2 damage to all enemy minions.
flavorText: Ancient pandaren proverb: He who is without secrets lacks flak.

name: Apexis Smuggler
text: After you play a Secret, Discover a spell.
flavorText: "S-secrets? I don't have any! Whoa, look, a spell!"

name: Astromancer Solarian
text: Spell Damage +1 Deathrattle: Shuffle 'Solarian Prime' into your deck.
flavorText: Loyal to Kael'thas Sunstrider, this blood elf mage sought arcane power in the Void. Did she find it... or did IT find her?

name: Evocation
text: Fill your hand with random Mage spells. At the end of your turn, discard them.
flavorText: You too could be the winner of the national spelling spree!

name: Incanter's Flow
text: Reduce the Cost of spells in your deck by (1).
flavorText: "Gettin' them discounts in bulk amounts, spells can come, and spells can go, castin' costs drop with my sweet, sweet flow."

name: Starscryer
text: Deathrattle: Draw a spell.
flavorText: Often grieves with the Starsweeper.

name: Cram Session
text: Draw 1 (card, cards) (improved by Spell Damage).
flavorText: The font of the arcane gives nearly limitless access to power and energy! But it can't keep you awake, for that we still use coffee.

name: Confection Cyclone
text: Battlecry: Add two 1/2 Sugar Elementals to your hand.
flavorText: "Oh, I thought it was a desert elemental?"

name: Conjure Mana Biscuit
text: Add a Biscuit to your hand that refreshes 2 Mana Crystals.
flavorText: So THIS is why she was AFK.

name: Deck of Lunacy
text: Transform spells in your deck into ones that cost (3) more. (They keep their original Cost.)
flavorText: Voted "Most Lunacy" in Madness Monthly magazine.

name: Game Master
text: The first Secret you play each turn costs (1).
flavorText: "You hear the mrgrgls of angry murlocs approaching. Roll initiative!"

name: Arcane Intellect
text: Draw 2 cards.
flavorText: Playing this card makes you SMARTER. And let's face it: we could all stand to be a little smarter.

name: Frost Nova
text: Freeze all enemy minions.
flavorText: Hey man, that's cold. Literally and metaphorically.

name: Counterspell
text: Secret: When your opponent casts a spell, Counter it.
flavorText: What's the difference between a mage playing with Counterspell and a mage who isn't? The mage who isn't is getting Pyroblasted in the face.

name: Ice Barrier
text: Secret: When your hero is attacked, gain 8 Armor.
flavorText: This is Rank 1. Rank 2 is Chocolate Milk Barrier.

name: Kirin Tor Mage
text: Battlecry: The next Secret you play this turn costs (0).
flavorText: The Kirin Tor reside in the floating city of Dalaran. How do you make a Dalaran float? Two scoops of ice cream, one scoop of Dalaran.

name: Mirror Entity
text: Secret: After your opponent plays a minion, summon a copy of it.
flavorText: "You go first." - Krush'gor the Behemoth, to his pet boar.

name: Spellbender
text: Secret: When an enemy casts a spell on a minion, summon a 1/3 as the new target.
flavorText: While it's fun to intercept enemy lightning bolts, a spellbender much prefers to intercept opposing Marks of the Wild. It just feels meaner. And blood elves... well, they're a little mean.

name: Vaporize
text: Secret: When a minion attacks your hero, destroy it.
flavorText: Rumor has it that Deathwing brought about the Cataclysm after losing a game to this card. We may never know the truth.

name: Messenger Raven
text: Battlecry: Discover a Mage minion.
flavorText: You can make a collect CAW!

name: Dune Sculptor
text: After you cast a spell, add a random Mage minion to your hand.
flavorText: Come for the magic show, stay for the sand castles.

name: Flame Ward
text: Secret: After a minion attacks your hero, deal 3 damage to all enemy minions.
flavorText: Not to be confused with the burn ward.

name: Chenvaala
text: After you cast three spells in a turn, summon a 5/5 Elemental.
flavorText: Like the Dragon Soul. If dragons had souls of ice.

name: Arcane Amplifier
text: Your Hero Power deals 2 extra damage.
flavorText: Not on good terms with warlocks.

name: Imprisoned Observer
text: Dormant for 2 turns. When this awakens, deal 2 damage to all enemy minions.
flavorText: Currently serving two turns on charges of aggravated minion slaughter.

name: Netherwind Portal
text: Secret: After your opponent casts a spell, summon a random 4-Cost minion.
flavorText: More aromatic than a regular portal.

name: Combustion
text: Deal 4 damage to a minion. Any excess damages both neighbors.
flavorText: Sally is friends with three Silverhand Recruits conveniently standing in a line. After casting this spell, how many friends does she have left? (Show your work.)

name: Firebrand
text: Spellburst: Deal 4 damage randomly split among all enemy minions.
flavorText: Too cool for school, too hot for thought.

name: Rigged Faire Game
text: Secret: If you didn't take any damage during your opponent's turn, draw 3 cards.
flavorText: What's faire is fair.

name: Fireball
text: Deal 6 damage.
flavorText: This spell is useful for burning things. If you're looking for spells that toast things, or just warm them a little, you're in the wrong place.

name: Polymorph
text: Transform a minion into a 1/1 Sheep.
flavorText: There was going to be a pun in this flavor text, but it just came out baa-d.

name: Water Elemental
text: Freeze any character damaged by this minion.
flavorText: Don't summon a water elemental at a party. It'll dampen the mood.

name: Cone of Cold
text: Freeze a minion and the minions next to it, and deal 1 damage to them.
flavorText: Magi of the Kirin Tor were casting Cubes of Cold for many years before Cones came into fashion some 90 years ago.

name: Ethereal Arcanist
text: If you control a Secret at the end of your turn, gain +2/+2.
flavorText: The ethereals are wrapped in cloth to give form to their non-corporeal bodies. Also because it's nice and soft.

name: Conjurer's Calling
text: Twinspell Destroy a minion. Summon 2 minions of the same Cost to replace it.
flavorText: If only you’d let it go to voicemail…

name: Kirin Tor Tricaster
text: Spell Damage +3 Your spells cost (1) more.
flavorText: The math checks out!

name: Azure Explorer
text: Spell Damage +2 Battlecry: Discover a Dragon.
flavorText: Has an appetite for knowledge!

name: Occult Conjurer
text: Battlecry: If you control a Secret, summon a copy of this.
flavorText: Like mirror image, but more secretive and angsty.

name: Ring Toss
text: Discover a Secret and cast it. Corrupt: Discover 2 instead.
flavorText: If you liked it, then you shoulda put a ring on it!

name: Cloud Prince
text: Battlecry: If you control a Secret, deal 6 damage.
flavorText: "In West Cloudidelphia, born and raised; flinging lightning for the rest of my days."

name: Naga Sand Witch
text: Battlecry: Change the Cost of spells in your hand to (5).
flavorText: 5 mana footlong, anyone?

name: Malygos, Aspect of Magic
text: Battlecry: If you're holding a Dragon, Discover an upgraded Mage spell.
flavorText: It's official. We can say Malygeese.

name: Rolling Fireball
text: Deal 8 damage to a minion. Any excess damage continues to the left or right.
flavorText: Why don't they ever run perpendicular?

name: Apexis Blast
text: Deal 5 damage. If your deck has no minions, summon a random 5-Cost minion.
flavorText: Lonely mages can still have a blast!

name: Mozaki, Master Duelist
text: After you cast a spell, gain Spell Damage +1.
flavorText: Treats her students like her peers, which means defeating them in one-sided duels all day long.

name: Wyrm Weaver
text: Spellburst: Summon two 1/3 Mana Wyrms.
flavorText: Studied basket weaving as an undergrad.

name: Firework Elemental
text: Battlecry: Deal 3 damage to a minion. Corrupt: Deal 12 instead.
flavorText: The brightest spark can still go dark.

name: Blizzard
text: Deal 2 damage to all enemy minions and Freeze them.
flavorText: This spell can be very Entertaining.

name: Reno the Relicologist
text: Battlecry: If your deck has no duplicates, deal 10 damage randomly split among all enemy minions.
flavorText: All his life, Reno Jackson was only a gatling wand away from becoming the greatest and most terrifying mage who ever existed.

name: Sayge, Seer of Darkmoon
text: Battlecry: Draw (card, cards). (Upgraded for each friendly Secret that has triggered this game!)
flavorText: There are no secrets between us... or refunds.

name: Flamestrike
text: Deal 4 damage to all enemy minions.
flavorText: When the ground is on fire, you should not stop, drop, and roll.

name: Archmage Antonidas
text: Whenever you cast a spell, add a 'Fireball' spell to your hand.
flavorText: Antonidas was the Grand Magus of the Kirin Tor, and Jaina's mentor. This was a big step up from being Grand Magus of Jelly Donuts.

name: Dragoncaster
text: Battlecry: If you're holding a Dragon, your next spell this turn costs (0).
flavorText: It’s challenging to perform magic on dragonback. It’s so easy to drop the rabbit.

name: Animated Avalanche
text: Battlecry: If you played an Elemental last turn, summon a copy of this.
flavorText: Always sliding down mountains because it can't stop talking with its hands.

name: Mask of C'Thun
text: Deal 10 damage randomly split among all enemies.
flavorText: Hide in the mask, but it will wear you. Through its gleaming eye, you shall see true.

name: Power of Creation
text: Discover a 6-Cost minion. Summon two copies of it.
flavorText: Mostly used for party tricks, to be honest.

name: Tortollan Pilgrim
text: Battlecry: Discover a spell in your deck and cast it with random targets.
flavorText: A tortollan made it to the desert!

name: Mana Giant
text: Costs (1) less for each card you've played this game that didn't start in your deck.
flavorText: Spell more and save more with a GIANT discount!

name: Deep Freeze
text: Freeze an enemy. Summon two 3/6 Water Elementals.
flavorText: "Dancing with the Satyrs… on Ice!"

name: Grand Finale
text: Summon an 8/8 Elemental. Repeat for each Elemental you played last turn.
flavorText: Considering all the other hazards at Darkmoon, overindulgent pyrotechnics seem downright pedestrian.

name: Pyroblast
text: Deal 10 damage.
flavorText: Take the time for an evil laugh after you draw this card.

name: Kalecgos
text: Your first spell each turn costs (0). Battlecry: Discover a spell.
flavorText: He was once the Aspect of Magic but gave it up to focus on cheap tricks.

name: Puzzle Box of Yogg-Saron
text: Cast 10 random spells (targets chosen randomly).
flavorText: "PUT THE BOX DOWN, RENO!"

name: The Amazing Reno
text: Battlecry: Make all minions disappear. *Poof!*
flavorText: "Reno!" "Please address me by my proper title." " Amazing Reno..."

name: First Day of School
text: Add 2 random 1-Cost minions to your hand.
flavorText: "Report to the bookstore to buy your books, the alchemist to buy your potions, and then get your wands at the… wandryroom?"

name: Blessing of Might
text: Give a minion +3 Attack.
flavorText: "As in, you MIGHT want to get out of my way." - Toad Mackle, recently buffed.

name: Hand of Protection
text: Give a minion Divine Shield.
flavorText: This spell has been renamed so many times, even paladins don’t know what it should be called anymore.

name: Humility
text: Change a minion's Attack to 1.
flavorText: This card makes something really damp. Oh wait. That's "Humidity."

name: Light's Justice
flavorText: Prince Malchezaar was a collector of rare weapons. He'd animate them and have them dance for him.

name: Blessing of Wisdom
text: Choose a minion. Whenever it attacks, draw a card.
flavorText: Apparently with wisdom comes the knowledge that you should probably be attacking every turn.

name: Eye for an Eye
text: Secret: When your hero takes damage, deal that much damage to the enemy hero.
flavorText: Justice sometimes takes the form of a closed fist into a soft cheek.

name: Noble Sacrifice
text: Secret: When an enemy attacks, summon a 2/1 Defender as the new target.
flavorText: We will always remember you, "Defender!"

name: Redemption
text: Secret: When a friendly minion dies, return it to life with 1 Health.
flavorText: I am not sure how you get demptioned the first time. It’s a mystery!

name: Repentance
text: Secret: After your opponent plays a minion, reduce its Health to 1.
flavorText: Repentance often comes in the moment before obliteration. Curious.

name: Desperate Measures
text: Twinspell Cast a random Paladin Secret.
flavorText: Desperate times call for disparate secrets.

name: Never Surrender!
text: Secret: When your opponent casts a spell, give your minions +2 Health.
flavorText: But sometimes concede.

name: Brazen Zealot
text: Whenever you summon a minion, gain +1 Attack.
flavorText: Some paladins really Light it up.

name: Making Mummies
text: Quest: Play 5 Reborn minions. Reward: Emperor Wraps.
flavorText: "I do say, this gives me the vapors every single time!"

name: Righteous Cause
text: Sidequest: Summon 5 minions. Reward: Give your minions +1/+1.
flavorText: "And I hereby dub thee a cadet of the Explorer’s League! NEXT!"

name: Sand Breath
text: Give a minion +1/+2. Give it Divine Shield if you're holding a Dragon.
flavorText: After Uldum, EVERYONE had sand breath.

name: Aldor Attendant
text: Battlecry: Reduce the Cost of your Librams by (1) this game.
flavorText: Will check to make sure you have a valid libramary card.

name: Imprisoned Sungill
text: Dormant for 2 turns. When this awakens, summon two 1/1 Murlocs.
flavorText: Imprisoned for ten thousand years! Not because it's a demon. Because of the dancing.

name: Shield of Honor
text: Give a damaged minion +3 Attack and Divine Shield.
flavorText: "Sir, this shield would've been more helpful last turn!"

name: Wave of Apathy
text: Set the Attack of all enemy minions to 1 until your next turn.
flavorText: "Flavor text? Eh. Can’t be bothered."

name: Oh My Yogg!
text: Secret: When your opponent casts a spell, they instead cast a random one of the same Cost.
flavorText: Many wonders lie within, but they are not mere toys when your mind is their plaything.

name: Holy Light
text: Restore 6 Health.
flavorText: If you are often bathed in Holy Light, you should consider wearing sunscreen.

name: Argent Protector
text: Battlecry: Give a friendly minion Divine Shield.
flavorText: "I'm not saying you can dodge fireballs. I'm saying with this shield, you won't have to."

name: Lightforged Blessing
text: Twinspell Give a friendly minion Lifesteal.
flavorText: Some might call this a lightforgery.

name: Mysterious Blade
text: Battlecry: If you control a Secret, gain +1 Attack.
flavorText: It knows every secret you have left.

name: Micro Mummy
text: Reborn At the end of your turn, give another random friendly minion +1 Attack.
flavorText: The dramatically detailed terrifically trimmed replica of the real thing!

name: Sandwasp Queen
text: Battlecry: Add two 2/1 Sandwasps to your hand.
flavorText: Oooh, see that wasp! Watch that sting! Dig in the Sandwasp Queen!

name: Sir Finley of the Sands
text: Battlecry: If your deck has no duplicates, Discover an upgraded Hero Power.
flavorText: "The sands shall be my sea! And this scarab shall be my, er, strange and wriggly boat!"

name: Subdue
text: Set a minion's Attack and Health to 1.
flavorText: Like humility but more humiliating.

name: Sanctuary
text: Sidequest: Take no damage for a turn. Reward: Summon a 3/6 minion with Taunt.
flavorText: Few quests are completed by cowering under a table.

name: Air Raid
text: Twinspell Summon two 1/1 Silver Hand Recruits with Taunt.
flavorText: It's difficult to get an air raid together. You have to get twenty-five people, and they all want to play a paladin!

name: Shotbot
text: Reborn
flavorText: Impact detected. Assuming hero pose.

name: Hand of A'dal
text: Give a minion +2/+2. Draw a card.
flavorText: When it meets the Hand of Gul'dan, they're SHAKING.

name: Libram of Wisdom
text: Give a minion +1/+1 and "Deathrattle: Add a 'Libram of Wisdom' spell to your hand."
flavorText: The best wisdom is passed on.

name: Murgur Murgurgle
text: Divine Shield Deathrattle: Shuffle 'Murgurgle Prime' into your deck.
flavorText: Murlocs are not native to Outland. When the Sungills arrived, one among them rose to the challenge of this dark world. They call him... Murgurgle. Murgur Murgurgle.

name: Argent Braggart
text: Battlecry: Gain Attack and Health to match the highest in the battlefield.
flavorText: Not sure why he's bragging, he's got the same stats as the next guy.

name: Redscale Dragontamer
text: Deathrattle: Draw a Dragon.
flavorText: Sir Finley made this look a lot easier three expansions ago...

name: Snack Run
text: Discover a spell. Restore Health to your hero equal to its Cost.
flavorText: "I'll have two monster churros, a combo box of Yogg-Saron, and one of those turkey legs that ate the Silver Hand Recruit."

name: Aldor Peacekeeper
text: Battlecry: Change an enemy minion's Attack to 1.
flavorText: The Aldor hate two things: the Scryers and smooth jazz.

name: Sword of Justice
text: After you summon a minion, give it +1/+1 and this loses 1 Durability.
flavorText: I dub you Sir Loin of Beef!

name: Bronze Herald
text: Deathrattle: Add two 4/4 Dragons to your hand.
flavorText: This is why you shouldn’t shoot the messenger.

name: Call to Adventure
text: Draw the lowest Cost minion from your deck. Give it +2/+2.
flavorText: Even the smallest minion can change the outcome of the game.

name: Commander Rhyssa
text: Your Secrets trigger twice.
flavorText: Two people can keep a secret as long as neither of them are Commander Rhyssa.

name: Salhet's Pride
text: Deathrattle: Draw two 1-Health minions from your deck.
flavorText: Pride cometh before the maul.

name: Bronze Explorer
text: Lifesteal Battlecry: Discover a Dragon.
flavorText: Always ready to explore new friendships! Except with Deathwing.

name: Dragonrider Talritha
text: Deathrattle: Give a Dragon in your hand +3/+3 and this Deathrattle.
flavorText: You can't just run away from your problems. Unless you have another dragon to jump to.

name: Sky Claw
text: Your other Mechs have +1 Attack. Battlecry: Summon two 1/1 Microcopters.
flavorText: Carefully engineered to never grab the Mimiron plush toy.

name: Underlight Angling Rod
text: After your Hero attacks, add a random Murloc to your hand.
flavorText: "I said I wanted the ASHbringer not FISHbringer!"

name: Ceremonial Maul
text: Spellburst: Summon a Student with Taunt and stats equal to the spell's Cost.
flavorText: For the most discerning of hall monitors.

name: Gift of Luminance
text: Give a minion Divine Shield, then summon a 1/1 copy of it.
flavorText: You get a small version of yourself in a snow globe to remember the moment.

name: Goody Two-Shields
text: Divine Shield Spellburst: Gain Divine Shield.
flavorText: These are my shields. There are at least two like them, and both are mine.

name: Lord Barov
text: Battlecry: Set the Health of all other minions to 1. Deathrattle: Deal 1 damage to all minions.
flavorText: Alexei Barov stayed at Scholomance despite leasing it to Kel’Thuzad. He says it’s for "supervision."

name: Carnival Barker
text: Whenever you summon a 1-Health minion, give it +1/+2.
flavorText: The barking initially confused faire-goers, so he switched to words.

name: Day at the Faire
text: Summon 3 Silver Hand Recruits. Corrupt: Summon 5.
flavorText: Karl knew he would someday regret that turkey leg.

name: Imprisoned Celestial
text: Dormant for 2 turns. Spellburst: Give your minions Divine Shield.
flavorText: "Look at your deck, now back to me, now back at your deck, now back to me. Who am I? None of your—I'm on a horse."

name: Blessing of Kings
text: Give a minion +4/+4. (+4 Attack/+4 Health)
flavorText: Given the number of kings who have been assassinated, are you sure you want their blessing?

name: Consecration
text: Deal 2 damage to all enemies.
flavorText: Consecrated ground glows with Holy energy. But it smells a little, too.

name: Hammer of Wrath
text: Deal 3 damage. Draw a card.
flavorText: A good paladin has many tools. Hammer of Wrath, Pliers of Vengeance, Hacksaw of Justice, etc.

name: Truesilver Champion
text: Whenever your hero attacks, restore 2 Health to it.
flavorText: It Slices, it Dices. You can cut a tin can with it. (But you wouldn't want to.)

name: Equality
text: Change the Health of ALL minions to 1.
flavorText: We are all special unique snowflakes... with 1 Health.

name: Ancestral Guardian
text: Lifesteal Reborn
flavorText: No one knows whose ancestor he is, but he's still upset that you never call.

name: Lightforged Zealot
text: Battlecry: If your deck has no Neutral cards, equip a   4/2 Truesilver Champion.
flavorText: Card-carrying member of the Paladins Only Paladin Club.

name: Nozdormu the Timeless
text: Battlecry: Set each player to 10 Mana Crystals.
flavorText: Time is mana!

name: High Abbess Alura
text: Spellburst: Cast a spell from your deck (targets this if possible).
flavorText: She's all about hitting the books. Literally.

name: Balloon Merchant
text: Battlecry: Give your Silver Hand Recruits +1 Attack and Divine Shield.
flavorText: It's a shiny yellow balloon! But it can be popped with a single point of damage.

name: Blessed Champion
text: Double a minion's Attack.
flavorText: This card causes double the trouble AND double the fun.

name: Holy Wrath
text: Draw a card and deal damage equal to its Cost.
flavorText: C'mon Molten Giant!!

name: Righteousness
text: Give your minions Divine Shield.
flavorText: Shield yourself in righteousness! It feels like a warm fuzzy blanket.

name: Dragon Speaker
text: Battlecry: Give all Dragons in your hand +3/+3.
flavorText: All of his speeches really drag on.

name: Duel!
text: Summon a minion from each player's deck. They fight!
flavorText: If you don’t fight to the death, it’s Duel Yielding.

name: Amber Watcher
text: Battlecry: Restore 8 Health.
flavorText: Healing really resin-ates with him.

name: Scalelord
text: Battlecry: Give your Murlocs Divine Shield.
flavorText: It's about what they have in common, not what makes them different.

name: Aldor Truthseeker
text: Taunt. Battlecry: Reduce the Cost of your Librams by (2) this game.
flavorText: It’s under 'T.'

name: Libram of Justice
text: Equip a 1/4 weapon. Change the Health of all enemy minions to 1.
flavorText: Proper justice. Throw the book at him!

name: Blessing of Authority
text: Give a minion +8/+8. It can't attack heroes this turn.
flavorText: A paladin fights with honor! We don't go face... until next turn!

name: Carousel Gryphon
text: Divine Shield Corrupt: Gain +3/+3 and Taunt.
flavorText: "When does this bird land in Stormwind? I've been flying for hours!"

name: Lothraxion the Redeemed
text: Battlecry: For the rest of the game, after you summon a Silver Hand Recruit, give it Divine Shield.
flavorText: So infused with the Light, he has to wear double sleep masks at night.

name: Avenging Wrath
text: Deal 8 damage randomly split among all enemies.
flavorText: Wham! Wham! Wham! Wham! Wham! Wham! Wham! Wham!

name: Pharaoh's Blessing
text: Give a minion +4/+4, Divine Shield, and Taunt.
flavorText: Life hack: Sneeze near a pharaoh.

name: Devout Pupil
text: Divine Shield, Taunt Costs (1) less for each spell you've cast on friendly characters this game.
flavorText: He considers textbooks Light reading.

name: Judicious Junior
text: Lifesteal
flavorText: She's judge, jury, and junior!

name: Hammer of the Naaru
text: Battlecry: Summon a 6/6 Holy Elemental with Taunt.
flavorText: The naaru wasn't using it. It doesn't have arms.

name: Guardian of Kings
text: Battlecry: Restore 6 Health to your hero.
flavorText: Holy beings from the beyond are so cliché!

name: Lightforged Crusader
text: Battlecry: If your deck has no Neutral cards, add 5 random Paladin cards to your hand.
flavorText: Self-appointed president of the Paladins Only Paladin Club.

name: Lady Liadrin
text: Battlecry: Add a copy of each spell you cast on friendly characters this game to your hand.
flavorText: When it comes to spells, she loves 'em then she librams.

name: Commencement
text: Summon a minion from your deck. Give it Taunt and Divine Shield.
flavorText: "Remember, graduates—you carry a heavy weight on your shoulders now."

name: Libram of Judgment
text: Corrupt: Gain Lifesteal.
flavorText: You really can't judge a book by its cover.

name: Lay on Hands
text: Restore 8 Health. Draw 3 cards.
flavorText: A grammatically awkward life saver.

name: Tirion Fordring
text: Divine Shield, Taunt Deathrattle: Equip a 5/3 Ashbringer.
flavorText: If you haven't heard the Tirion Fordring theme song, it's because it doesn't exist.

name: Tip the Scales
text: Summon 7 Murlocs from your deck.
flavorText: Hold on, I need to get some murlocs to weigh in on this.

name: Turalyon, the Tenured
text: Rush. Whenever this attacks a minion, set the defender's Attack and Health to 3.
flavorText: "Let evil flee before righteousness; let the innocent live in peace. Let the day come when none need fear. For that day, I give my life gladly."

name: High Exarch Yrel
text: Battlecry: If your deck has no Neutral cards, gain Rush, Lifesteal, Taunt, and Divine Shield.
flavorText: There can be no neutrality in the fight against darkness.

name: Libram of Hope
text: Restore 8 Health. Summon an 8/8 Guardian with Taunt and Divine Shield.
flavorText: "Think you got lethal? Libram of NOPE!"

name: Nozari
text: Battlecry: Restore both heroes to full Health.
flavorText: In another timeline, she was called Yeszari.

name: Power Word: Shield
text: Give a minion +2 Health.
flavorText: Sure the extra protection is nice, but the shield really reduces visibility.

name: Circle of Healing
text: Restore 4 Health to ALL minions.
flavorText: It isn't really a circle.

name: Silence
text: Silence a minion.
flavorText: Reserved for enemy spellcasters, evil liches from beyond the grave, and karaoke nights at the Grim Guzzler.

name: Forbidden Words
text: Spend all your Mana. Destroy a minion with that much Attack or less.
flavorText: Please confirm your age before reading this flavor text.

name: Lazul's Scheme
text: Reduce the Attack of an enemy minion by 1 until your next turn. (Upgrades each turn!)
flavorText: "What's that you're dreaming? You're weak and you're screaming! It must be my scheming..."

name: Whispers of EVIL
text: Add a Lackey to your hand.
flavorText: Madame Lazul’s ASMR program is off to a promising start!

name: Raise Dead
text: Deal 3 damage to your hero. Return two friendly minions that died this game to your hand.
flavorText: Technically, it’s just really late healing.

name: Holy Smite
text: Deal 3 damage to a minion.
flavorText: It doesn't matter how pious you are. Everyone needs a good smiting now and again.

name: Mind Vision
text: Put a copy of a random card in your opponent's hand into your hand.
flavorText: I see what you did there.

name: Psychic Conjurer
text: Battlecry: Copy a card in your opponent’s deck and add it to your hand.
flavorText: "I see... a WISP? Why do you have a wisp?!"

name: Radiance
text: Restore 5 Health to your hero.
flavorText: Because you're worth it!

name: Inner Fire
text: Change a minion's Attack to be equal to its Health.
flavorText: Good idea: Buffing your minions. Bad idea: Starting a conversation in the Barrens.

name: Scarlet Subjugator
text: Battlecry: Give an enemy minion -2 Attack until your next turn.
flavorText: At the Scarlet Monastery, he learned the sacred art of kicking people when they're up.

name: Activate the Obelisk
text: Quest: Restore 15 Health. Reward: Obelisk's Eye.
flavorText: A one-eyed, one stone, towering purple minion healer.

name: Embalming Ritual
text: Give a minion Reborn.
flavorText: "Guess what! We're getting a new cat."

name: Disciple of Galakrond
text: Battlecry: Invoke Galakrond.
flavorText: Raising Galakrond will cause thurible, thurible damage.

name: Cleric of Scales
text: Battlecry: If you're holding a Dragon, Discover a spell from your deck.
flavorText: If she can't find a spell, it's a clerical error.

name: Imprisoned Homunculus
text: Dormant for 2 turns. Taunt
flavorText: He got a time out for excessive vulgarity.

name: Reliquary of Souls
text: Lifesteal Deathrattle: Shuffle 'Reliquary Prime' into your deck.
flavorText: These three represent Anger, Desire, and Suffering. Much like raid night guild chat.

name: Renew
text: Restore 3 Health. Discover a spell.
flavorText: I am rejuvenated, I am renewed, I am my own nightlight!

name: Draconic Studies
text: Discover a Dragon. Your next one costs (1) less.
flavorText: Our Draconic Studies program has a high rate of burnout.

name: Frazzled Freshman
flavorText: "Late to bed, early to rise, makes a student unable to open her eyes."

name: Shadow Word: Death
text: Destroy a minion with 5 or more Attack.
flavorText: If you miss, it leaves a lightning-bolt-shaped scar on your target.

name: Shadow Word: Pain
text: Destroy a minion with 3 or less Attack.
flavorText: A step up from a spell cast by many beginning acolytes: "Shadow Word: Annoy".

name: Kul Tiran Chaplain
text: Battlecry: Give a friendly minion +2 Health.
flavorText: The maritime Kul Tiran clergy are unique among priests for using holy saltwater.

name: Lightwell
text: At the start of your turn, restore 3 Health to a damaged friendly character.
flavorText: It isn't clear if people ignore the Lightwell, or if it is just invisible.

name: Thoughtsteal
text: Copy 2 cards in your opponent's deck and add them to your hand.
flavorText: "What do you get when you cast Thoughtsteal on an Orc? Nothing!" - Tauren joke

name: EVIL Conscripter
text: Deathrattle: Add a Lackey to your hand.
flavorText: Kobold! There’s a place you can handle I said kobold! When you’re short in the candle Cast a spell with the E! V! I! L!

name: Shadowy Figure
text: Battlecry: Transform into a 2/2 copy of a friendly Deathrattle minion.
flavorText: Terrible at shadow puppets: “This is… a tentacle! And this is… two tentacles!”

name: Grandmummy
text: Reborn Deathrattle: Give a random friendly minion +1/+1.
flavorText: A grandmummy’s love is eternal.

name: Holy Ripple
text: Deal 1 damage to all enemies. Restore 1 Health to all friendly characters.
flavorText: I still prefer the taste of banana fudge ripple.

name: Penance
text: Lifesteal Deal 3 damage to a minion.
flavorText: This is what happens when you don’t give a sincere apology.

name: Envoy of Lazul
text: Battlecry: Look at 3 cards. Guess which one is in your opponent's hand to get a copy of it.
flavorText: "Note to self: possess someone who's local and knows directions next time."

name: Dragonmaw Sentinel
text: Battlecry: If you're holding a Dragon, gain +1 Attack and Lifesteal.
flavorText: On the side, she's training for the annual Dragonmaw hammer throw tournament.

name: Sethekk Veilweaver
text: After you cast a spell on a minion, add a Priest spell to your hand.
flavorText: The Sethekk weren't able to survive this long by being wasteful with their power. Or their wacky hats.

name: Power Word: Feast
text: Give a minion +2/+2. Restore it to full Health at the end of this turn.
flavorText: Some people are here for the stellar, world-renowned academic program. Others are here for the buffet.

name: Insight
text: Draw a minion. Corrupt: Reduce its Cost by (2).
flavorText: Shouldn't the eyes be facing backwards for insight?

name: Shadow Madness
text: Gain control of an enemy minion with 3 or less Attack until end of turn.
flavorText: You can rationalize it all you want, it's still a mean thing to do.

name: Madame Lazul
text: Battlecry: Discover a copy of a card in your opponent's hand.
flavorText: Of course she knows the future, she’s been looking at your cards the WHOLE TIME!

name: Wretched Reclaimer
text: Battlecry: Destroy a friendly minion, then return it to life with full Health.
flavorText: "Ok, here's the plan. We kill you, then bring you back." "Stronger?" "No, about the same."

name: Breath of the Infinite
text: Deal 2 damage to all minions. If you're holding a Dragon, only damage enemies.
flavorText: It's called "circular breathing."

name: Mindflayer Kaahrj
text: Battlecry: Choose an enemy minion. Deathrattle: Summon a new copy of it.
flavorText: It’s pronounced "Kaahrj."

name: Dark Prophecy
text: Discover a 2-Cost minion. Summon it and give it +3 Health.
flavorText: It's always a dark prophecy with Madame Lazul. Where's my happy, fluffy prophecy?!

name: Apotheosis
text: Give a minion +2/+3 and Lifesteal.
flavorText: Defined as the absolute pinnacle of existence. Plus Lifesteal.

name: Dragonmaw Overseer
text: At the end of your turn, give another friendly minion +2/+2.
flavorText: Ah, the Booterang... nothing cures peon laziness faster.

name: Mindrender Illucia
text: Battlecry: Swap hands and decks with your opponent until your next turn.
flavorText: "…and that's how I ended up with a Murloc Cultural Studies major."

name: Fairground Fool
text: Taunt Corrupt: Gain +4 Health.
flavorText: "What did Illidan say when his rocketeer broke down on the Darkmoon racetrack? YOU ARE NOT REPAIRED!"

name: Nazmani Bloodweaver
text: After you cast a spell, reduce the cost of a random card in your hand by (1).
flavorText: Her first stage name, Ketchupweaver, failed to excite the audience.

name: Palm Reading
text: Discover a spell. Reduce the Cost of spells in your hand by (1).
flavorText: Actual palms not required.

name: Holy Nova
text: Deal 2 damage to all enemy minions. Restore 2 Health to all friendly characters.
flavorText: If the Holy Light forsakes you, good luck casting this spell. Also, you're probably a jerk.

name: Power Infusion
text: Give a minion +2/+6.
flavorText: It infuses, it enthuses, it amuses!

name: Lightspawn
text: This minion's Attack is always equal to its Health.
flavorText: Spawn of the Light? Or Pawn of the Lights?

name: Mass Dispel
text: Silence all enemy minions. Draw a card.
flavorText: It dispels buffs, powers, hopes, and dreams.

name: Mindgames
text: Put a copy of a random minion from your opponent's deck into the battlefield.
flavorText: Sometimes it feels like this is all a game.

name: Shadow Word: Ruin
text: Destroy all minions with 5 or more Attack.
flavorText: Discovered by a worgen priest after a giant spilled a drink on her new white robes.

name: Hench-Clan Shadequill
text: Deathrattle: Restore 5 Health to the enemy hero.
flavorText: The Hench-Clan has a point.

name: Unsleeping Soul
text: Silence a friendly minion, then summon a copy of it.
flavorText: It's 3 am. Do you know where your soul is?

name: High Priest Amet
text: Whenever you summon a minion, set its Health equal to this minion's.
flavorText: All minions are equal, but some minions are more equal than others.

name: Psychopomp
text: Battlecry: Summon a random friendly minion that died this game. Give it Reborn.
flavorText: "Come with me if you want to re-live."

name: Fate Weaver
text: Battlecry: If you've Invoked twice, reduce the Cost of cards in your hand by (1).
flavorText: Do not draw the attention of a Fate Weaver, for it will always loom over your destiny.

name: Grave Rune
text: Give a minion "Deathrattle: Summon 2 copies of this."
flavorText: I'm gravely sorry to rune this.

name: Brittlebone Destroyer
text: Battlecry: If your hero's Health changed this turn, destroy a minion.
flavorText: Broke many a leg in drama class.

name: Cabal Acolyte
text: Taunt Spellburst: Gain control of a random enemy minion with 2 or less Attack.
flavorText: How did he get to the top of his class? He pulled a few strings!

name: Disciplinarian Gandling
text: After you play a minion, destroy it and summon a 4/4 Failed Student.
flavorText: "He doesn’t grade on a curve, but on a sharp spike instead."

name: Auspicious Spirits
text: Summon a random 4-Cost minion. Corrupt: Summon a 7-Cost minion instead.
flavorText: "I'm not AWE-spicious, but I am a little spicious."

name: Lightsteed
text: Your healing effects also give affected minions +2 Health.
flavorText: All the steed, half the calories.

name: The Nameless One
text: Battlecry: Choose a minion. Become a 4/4 copy of it, then Silence it.
flavorText: Used to be called " , the Nameless," but everyone got confused.

name: Temple Enforcer
text: Battlecry: Give a friendly minion +3 Health.
flavorText: He also moonlights Thursday nights as a bouncer at the Pig and Whistle Tavern.

name: Convincing Infiltrator
text: Taunt Deathrattle: Destroy a random enemy minion.
flavorText: It’s always nice to steal a familiar face.

name: Sandhoof Waterbearer
text: At the end of your turn, restore 5 Health to a damaged friendly character.
flavorText: Used to carrying for his team.

name: Chronobreaker
text: Deathrattle: If you're holding a Dragon, deal 3 damage to all enemy minions.
