flavorText: If he asks to borrow your watch, just say no.

name: Time Rip
text: Destroy a minion. Invoke Galakrond.
flavorText: "It's time. R.I.P."

name: Psyche Split
text: Give a minion +1/+2. Summon a copy of it.
flavorText: This is how the arakkoa make friends.

name: Dark Inquisitor Xanesh
text: Battlecry: Reduce the Cost of all Corrupt cards in your hand and deck by (2).
flavorText: Fear is the mind-killer, and also the name of my wurm.

name: Fortune Teller
text: Taunt Battlecry: Gain +1/+1 for each spell in your hand.
flavorText: "I see a giant piano in your future."

name: Cabal Shadow Priest
text: Battlecry: Take control of an enemy minion that has 2 or less Attack.
flavorText: You never know who may be secretly working for the Cabal....

name: Aeon Reaver
text: Battlecry: Deal damage to a minion equal to its Attack.
flavorText: Ripping centuries asunder helps him manage his busy schedule.

name: Initiation
text: Deal 4 damage to a minion. If that kills it, summon a new copy.
flavorText: The things a murloc's gotta go through to graduate from Scholomance…

name: Galakrond, the Unspeakable
text: Battlecry: Destroy 1 random enemy minion. ( )
flavorText: Lazul called Galakrond’s name, her voice echoed by whispers from the deep. Both of Galakrond’s eyes opened… and then other eyes opened, as well.

name: Skeletal Dragon
text: Taunt At the end of your turn, add a Dragon to your hand.
flavorText: I wish to complain about this dragon what I purchased not half an hour ago from this very boutique.

name: Soul Mirror
text: Summon copies of enemy minions. They attack their copies.
flavorText: It’s a doppelgang-war!

name: Natalie Seline
text: Battlecry: Destroy a minion and gain its Health.
flavorText: She discovered Xal'atath, Blade of the Black Empire, a terrible weapon of shadow magic that could both swallow a soul and cut a mean julienne.

name: Catrina Muerte
text: At the end of your turn, summon a friendly minion that died this game.
flavorText: She always manages to lift your spirits.

name: Murozond the Infinite
text: Battlecry: Play all cards your opponent played last turn.
flavorText: "Well, I'm glad YOU knew what I should be doing this turn."

name: Flesh Giant
text: Costs (1) less for each time your hero's Health changed during your turns.
flavorText: "A BIG mistake."

name: G'huun the Blood God
text: Battlecry: Draw 2 cards. They cost Health instead of Mana.
flavorText: All of the other Old Gods used to laugh and call him names. They never let poor G'huun join in any Old God games.

name: Idol of Y'Shaarj
text: Summon a 10/10 copy of a minion in your deck.
flavorText: Without a tongue, it speaks in seven. Without a voice, its echo lingers forever.

name: Mass Resurrection
text: Summon 3 friendly minions that died this game.
flavorText: One's company, two's a crowd, and three's a “mass” resurrection, apparently.

name: Plague of Death
text: Silence and destroy all minions.
flavorText: Don't worry, there's a happy little funhouse right under that sand pit.

name: Blood of G'huun
text: Taunt At the end of your turn, summon a 5/5 copy of a minion in your deck.
flavorText: An attempted cure becomes disease, blooming and thriving as rot and decay.

name: Mind Control
text: Take control of an enemy minion.
flavorText: Nominated as "Spell Most Likely to Make Your Opponent Punch the Wall."

name: Backstab
text: Deal 2 damage to an undamaged minion.
flavorText: It's funny how often yelling "Look over there!" gets your opponent to turn around.

name: Preparation
text: The next spell you cast this turn costs (2) less.
flavorText: "Be Prepared" - Rogue Motto

name: Shadowstep
text: Return a friendly minion to your hand. It costs (2) less.
flavorText: Rogue dance troops will sometimes Shadowstep away at the end of a performance. Crowds love it.

name: Deadly Poison
text: Give your weapon +2 Attack.
flavorText: Rogues guard the secrets to poison-making carefully, lest magi start incorporating poison into their spells. Poisonbolt? Rain of Poison? Poison Elemental? Nobody wants that.

name: Sinister Strike
text: Deal 3 damage to the enemy hero.
flavorText: There's something about this strike that just feels off. Sinister, even.

name: Pilfer
text: Add a random card from another class to your hand.
flavorText: The class is always greener on the other side of the board.

name: Daring Escape
text: Return all friendly minions to your hand.
flavorText: Impossible to cast without cackling evilly.

name: Togwaggle's Scheme
text: Choose a minion. Shuffle 1 (copy, copies) of it into your deck. (Upgrades each turn!)
flavorText: "Many minions equals many treasures for king. Kobold arithmetic!"

name: Bazaar Burglary
text: Quest: Add 4 cards from other classes to your hand. Reward: Ancient Blades.
flavorText: Just when you set up your "All-Natural Scented Candles" at the farmer's market and then some STUPID KOBOLD COMES AND TAKES THEM ALL!

name: Pharaoh Cat
text: Battlecry: Add a random Reborn minion to your hand.
flavorText: Mightiest of mousers, enduring in kingship of the upper and lower cat tree, conqueror of the red dot, the all-wise Catshepsut.

name: Plague of Madness
text: Each player equips a 2/2 Knife with Poisonous.
flavorText: Don't bring a candle to a knife fight.

name: Bloodsail Flybooter
text: Battlecry: Add two 1/1 Pirates to your hand.
flavorText: They’re pretty fly for some pirate guys.

name: Dragon's Hoard
text: Discover a Legendary minion from another class.
flavorText: The Alliance loves this hoard.

name: Praise Galakrond!
text: Give a minion +1 Attack. Invoke Galakrond.
flavorText: "Turn to Galakrond, Chapter 3 Verse 12. 'SNARL! ROAR! GRAAAAGH!' Let us reflect on this wisdom."

name: Blackjack Stunner
text: Battlecry: If you control a Secret, return a minion to its owner's hand. It costs (1) more.
flavorText: "I'm about to ruin this 10-cost minion's whole career."

name: Spymistress
text: Stealth
flavorText: Spies in Outland must blend into the environment. That means hot-pink gear and bright green hair. It’s a weird place.

name: Secret Passage
text: Replace your hand with 4 cards from your deck. Swap back next turn.
flavorText: I use this to sneak out at night and do some villainous baking in the kitchen.

name: Prize Plunderer
text: Combo: Deal 1 damage to a minion for each other card you've played this turn.
flavorText: But he'll never be able to plunder the prize of a happy childhood.

name: Sap
text: Return an enemy minion to your opponent's hand.
flavorText: Rogues love sappy movies.

name: Shiv
text: Deal 1 damage. Draw a card.
flavorText: Rogues are experts at SHIV-al-ry.

name: Betrayal
text: Force an enemy minion to deal its damage to the minions next to it.
flavorText: Everyone has a price. Gnomes, for example, can be persuaded by stuffed animals and small amounts of chocolate.

name: Cold Blood
text: Give a minion +2 Attack. Combo: +4 Attack instead.
flavorText: "I'm cold blooded, check it and see!"

name: Defias Ringleader
text: Combo: Summon a 2/1 Defias Bandit.
flavorText: He stole the deed to town years ago, so technically the town is his. He just calls people Scrub to be mean.

name: Eviscerate
text: Deal 2 damage. Combo: Deal 4 damage instead.
flavorText: There is a high cost to Eviscerating your opponent. You might tweak your elbow! That really hurts!

name: Patient Assassin
text: Stealth Poisonous
flavorText: He’s not really that patient. It just takes a while for someone to walk by that he can actually reach.

name: Underbelly Fence
text: Battlecry: If you're holding a card from another class,  gain +1/+1 and Rush.
flavorText: She’ll take anything you have—except scruples and a good work ethic.

name: Clever Disguise
text: Add 2 random spells from another class to your hand.
flavorText: "It me! Togwaggle!"

name: Whirlkick Master
text: Whenever you play a Combo card, add a random Combo card to your hand.
flavorText: C-c-combo!

name: Skyvateer
text: Stealth Deathrattle: Draw a card.
flavorText: When you go without fruits in an airship, you get a nasty case of skyvy.

name: Waxmancy
text: Discover a Battlecry minion. Reduce its Cost by (2).
flavorText: The waxmancer works with flame and form, giving shape to figures warm. Some think he's a crazy creeper, but crafting minions is simply cheaper.

name: Ambush
text: Secret: After your opponent plays a minion, summon a 2/3 Ambusher with Poisonous.
flavorText: Clip-clop clip-clop CLIP-CLOP STAB!

name: Ashtongue Slayer
text: Battlecry: Give a Stealthed minion +3 Attack and Immune this turn.
flavorText: Her other hand attachments include a corkscrew and a bottle opener.

name: Bamboozle
text: Secret: When one of your minions is attacked, transform it into a random one that costs (3) more.
flavorText: "WE DO YOU A BAMBOOZLE, HOOMAN!"

name: Dirty Tricks
text: Secret: After your opponent casts a spell, draw 2 cards.
flavorText: "Ahh sand in my eyes! Also, I'm being stabbed."

name: Shadowjeweler Hanar
text: After you play a Secret, Discover a Secret from a different class.
flavorText: What is a shadowjeweler? A miserable little pile of secrets.

name: Plagiarize
text: Secret: At the end of your opponent's turn, add copies of the cards they played to your hand.
flavorText: Copying is just using your resources wisely.

name: Foxy Fraud
text: Battlecry: Your next Combo card this turn costs (2) less.
flavorText: His other street con involves a druid. He can't pull it off without a plant.

name: Shadow Clone
text: Secret: After a minion attacks your hero, summon a copy of it with Stealth.
flavorText: "You thought you were attacking face, but it was me! You!"

name: Shenanigans
text: Secret: When your opponent draws their second card in a turn, transform it into a Banana.
flavorText: It's not personal, it's just monkey business.

name: Sweet Tooth
text: Corrupt: Gain +2 Attack and Stealth.
flavorText: He's been eyeballing that ice cream cone all day!

name: Swindle
text: Draw a spell. Combo: And a minion.
flavorText: You know, it's probably just cheaper to find a place that sells the plushie…

name: Tenwu of the Red Smoke
text: Battlecry: Return a friendly minion to your hand. It costs (1) this turn.
flavorText: Red, the color of subtlety.

name: Fan of Knives
text: Deal 1 damage to all enemy minions. Draw a card.
flavorText: I wouldn't say I LOVE knives, but I'm definitely a fan.

name: Headcrack
text: Deal 2 damage to the enemy hero. Combo: Return this to your hand next turn.
flavorText: When all else fails, nothing beats a swift whack upside the head.

name: Perdition's Blade
text: Battlecry: Deal 1 damage. Combo: Deal 2 instead.
flavorText: Perdition's Blade is Ragnaros's back-up weapon while Sulfuras is in the shop.

name: SI:7 Agent
text: Combo: Deal 2 damage.
flavorText: The agents of SI:7 are responsible for Stormwind's covert activities. Their duties include espionage, assassination, and throwing surprise birthday parties for the royal family.

name: EVIL Miscreant
text: Combo: Add two random Lackeys to your hand.
flavorText: Because there are no G.O.O.D. Miscreants.

name: Hooked Scimitar
text: Combo: Gain +2 Attack.
flavorText: Oooooooooooow. I'm hooked on a scimitar!

name: Seal Fate
text: Deal 3 damage to an undamaged character. Invoke Galakrond.
flavorText: Firmly press the seal of your fates instead of leaving the flap open.

name: Akama
text: Stealth Deathrattle: Shuffle 'Akama Prime' into your deck.
flavorText: "To many of my people, I am known as a traitor... as Illidan's lapdog. I will remain in the shadows, for now... Actually, maybe I'll just remain in the shadows forever."

name: Greyheart Sage
text: Battlecry: If you control a Stealthed minion, draw 2 cards.
flavorText: "What am I drinking again?"

name: Self-Sharpening Sword
text: After your hero attacks, gain +1 Attack.
flavorText: You no longer have to bring a stack of 2 swords to a test!

name: Vulpera Toxinblade
text: Your weapon has +2 Attack.
flavorText: The blade works well enough on its own… but this is just in case.

name: Cloak of Shadows
text: Give your hero Stealth for 1 turn.
flavorText: Only worthy emperors can see the cloak.

name: Sparkjoy Cheat
text: Battlecry: If you're holding a Secret, cast it and draw a card.
flavorText: "These do NOT spark joy!"

name: Ticket Master
text: Deathrattle: Shuffle 3 Tickets into your deck. When drawn, summon a 3/3 Plush Bear.
flavorText: You can exchange one ticket for a bear or save up thousands for a tacky light-up paperweight!

name: Plaguebringer
text: Battlecry: Give a friendly minion Poisonous.
flavorText: One sip and you've got the grippe.

name: Blade Flurry
text: Destroy your weapon and deal its damage to all enemy minions.
flavorText: "Look, it's not just about waving daggers around really fast. It's a lot more complicated than that." - Shan, Rogue Trainer

name: Edwin VanCleef
text: Combo: Gain +2/+2 for each other card you've played this turn.
flavorText: He led the Stonemasons in the reconstruction of Stormwind, and when the nobles refused to pay, he founded the Defias Brotherhood to, well, deconstruct Stormwind.

name: Master of Disguise
text: Battlecry: Give a friendly minion Stealth until your next turn.
flavorText: She's actually a male tauren. People don't call him "Master of Disguise" for nothing.

name: Hench-Clan Burglar
text: Battlecry: Discover a spell from another class.
flavorText: She’s more of a rat burglar.

name: Vendetta
text: Deal 4 damage to a minion. Costs (0) if you're holding a card from another class.
flavorText: A vengeful and vicarious vanguard against violent villains or vexed victims.

name: Waggle Pick
text: Deathrattle: Return a random friendly minion to your hand. It costs (2) less.
flavorText: Kobolds informally refer to its effect as a deathwaggle.

name: Sahket Sapper
text: Deathrattle: Return a  random enemy minion to  your opponent's hand.
flavorText: "Here, you dropped this."

name: Shadow of Death
text: Choose a minion. Shuffle 3 'Shadows' into your deck that summon a copy when drawn.
flavorText: Making new friends takes skill.

name: Umbral Skulker
text: Battlecry: If you've Invoked twice, add 3 Coins to your hand.
flavorText: "Three gold?! Do you have any idea how long this quest chain was?"

name: Infiltrator Lilian
text: Stealth Deathrattle: Summon a 4/2 Forsaken Lilian that attacks a random enemy.
flavorText: She'll get to the bottom of this even if it kills her. Twice!

name: Shifty Sophomore
text: Stealth Spellburst: Add a Combo card to your hand.
flavorText: Experienced enough to do crimes, inexperienced enough to be super obvious about it.

name: Assassin's Blade
flavorText: Guaranteed to have been owned by a real assassin. Certificate of authenticity included.

name: Assassinate
text: Destroy an enemy minion.
flavorText: If you don't want to be assassinated, move to the Barrens and change your name. Good luck!

name: Anka, the Buried
text: Battlecry: Change each Deathrattle minion in your hand into a 1/1 that costs (1).
flavorText: "You look familiar. Were you at my first funeral?"

name: Bazaar Mugger
text: Rush Battlecry: Add a random minion from another class to your hand.
flavorText: Premium muggings at a discount price.

name: Necrium Apothecary
text: Combo: Draw a Deathrattle minion from your deck and gain its Deathrattle.
flavorText: Necrium: Get the afterlife without the aftertaste!

name: Stowaway
text: Battlecry: If there are cards in your deck that didn't start there, draw 2 of them.
flavorText: Cut him a break. Even economy class tickets are pretty expensive these days.

name: Waxadred
text: Deathrattle: Shuffle a Candle into your deck that resummons Waxadred when drawn.
flavorText: Waxadred the dragon fought for his king, frolicking through the fields melting everything!

name: Shadow Sculptor
text: Combo: Draw a card for each card you've played this turn.
flavorText: Carving out new territory in the realm of shadow puppetry.

name: Malevolent Strike
text: Destroy a minion. Costs (1) less for each   card in your deck that   didn't start there.
flavorText: "I don't know how those got in there, but I'm blaming you two."

name: Kidnapper
text: Combo: Return a minion to its owner's hand.
flavorText: He just wants people to see his vacation photos.

name: Heistbaron Togwaggle
text: Battlecry: If you control a Lackey, choose a fantastic treasure.
flavorText: A staunch ally of Rafaam, at least while the shinies keep flowing.

name: Unidentified Contract
text: Destroy a minion. Gains a bonus effect in your hand.
flavorText: The terms of service are constantly changing.

name: Candle Breath
text: Draw 3 cards. Costs (3) less while you're holding a Dragon.
flavorText: "And Waxadred shall light their fires, with roaring breath hotter than pyres! Come before him, scamp and vandal, pledge your faith and lift your candle!"

name: Flik Skyshiv
text: Battlecry: Destroy a minion and all copies of it (wherever they are).
flavorText: Junior explorers scan the night sky in fear of her candle’s flame!

name: Grand Empress Shek'zara
text: Battlecry: Discover a card in your deck and draw all copies of it.
flavorText: So is a Grand Empress an empress that's grand or an empress's empress?

name: Sprint
text: Draw 4 cards.
flavorText: Rogues are not good joggers.

name: Tak Nozwhisker
text: Whenever you shuffle a card into your deck, add a copy to your hand.
flavorText: "One for me and one for future me!"

name: Galakrond, the Nightmare
text: Battlecry: Draw 1 card. It costs (1). ( )
flavorText: The enormous creature unfurled terrifying claws dripping with poisonous ichor. King Togwaggle was pleased, but inwardly disappointed the great Nightmare refused to wear the candle.

name: Cursed Vagrant
text: Deathrattle: Summon a 7/5 Shadow with Stealth.
flavorText: Little did he know… it was really the talbuk leg that was cursed.

name: Ancestral Healing
text: Restore a minion to full Health and give it Taunt.
flavorText: I personally prefer some non-ancestral right-the-heck-now healing, but maybe that is just me.

name: Totemic Might
text: Give your Totems +2 Health.
flavorText: Totem-stomping is no longer recommended.

name: Mutate
text: Transform a friendly minion into a random one that costs (1) more.
flavorText: You'll get the transformation you want when murlocs fly.

name: Totemic Surge
text: Give your Totems +2 Attack.
flavorText: It's not really advanced shamanic magic, you just draw nasty eyebrows on them.

name: Frost Shock
text: Deal 1 damage to an enemy character and Freeze it.
flavorText: FROST SHOCK!

name: Dust Devil
text: Windfury. Overload: (2)
flavorText: Westfall is full of dust devils. And buzzards. And crazed golems. And pirates. Why does anyone live here?

name: Earth Shock
text: Silence a minion, then deal 1 damage to it.
flavorText: Earth Shock? Shouldn't it be "Azeroth Shock"?

name: Forked Lightning
text: Deal 2 damage to 2 random enemy minions. Overload: (2)
flavorText: If you combine it with Spooned Lightning and Knived Lightning, you have the full dining set.

name: Lightning Bolt
text: Deal 3 damage. Overload: (1)
flavorText: Lightning Bolt! Lightning Bolt! Lightning Bolt!

name: Sludge Slurper
text: Battlecry: Add a Lackey to your hand. Overload: (1)
flavorText: You can't stop slurping this delicious sludge!

name: Corrupt the Waters
text: Quest: Play 6 Battlecry cards. Reward: Heart of Vir'naal.
flavorText: This is why Hagatha is banned from public pools.

name: Storm's Wrath
text: Give your minions +1/+1. Overload: (1)
flavorText: How many dragons does it take to destroy a hot air balloon? One, two, three, CRUNCH!

name: Surging Tempest
text: Has +1 Attack while you have Overloaded Mana Crystals.
flavorText: "Overloaded? Should've gotten a surge protector."

name: Revolve
text: Transform all minions into random ones with the same Cost.
flavorText: "Please don't ride the carousel for thirty minutes after eating. After the carousel eats, I mean."

name: Rockbiter Weapon
text: Give a friendly character +3 Attack this turn.
flavorText: This would be real handy if your enemy is made of rock.

name: Windfury
text: Give a minion Windfury.
flavorText: Windfury is like Earthfury and Firefury, but more light and airy.

name: Ancestral Spirit
text: Give a minion "Deathrattle: Resummon this minion."
flavorText: It was just a flesh wound.

name: Stormforged Axe
text: Overload: (1)
flavorText: Yo, that's a nice axe.

name: Soul of the Murloc
text: Give your minions "Deathrattle: Summon a 1/1 Murloc."
flavorText: Previously thought nonexistent.

name: Underbelly Angler
text: After you play a Murloc, add a random Murloc to your hand.
flavorText: Attracts murlocs… and moths.

name: Witch's Brew
text: Restore 4 Health. Repeatable this turn.
flavorText: The swill has eyes!

name: EVIL Totem
text: At the end of your turn, add a Lackey to your hand.
flavorText: A lot of people blame the parents when a totem goes bad.

name: Sandstorm Elemental
text: Battlecry: Deal 1 damage to all enemy minions. Overload: (1)
flavorText: Doot doot doot doot doot [Pause] Doot doot doot doot doot DEE doot doot doot doot doot!

name: Invocation of Frost
text: Freeze an enemy. Invoke Galakrond.
flavorText: Galakrond adores a little frosting.

name: Explosive Evolution
text: Transform a minion into a random one that costs (3) more.
flavorText: Let's give a big hand for goblin experimentation!

name: Diligent Notetaker
text: Spellburst: Return the spell to your hand.
flavorText: You never know what cards are going to be on the test.

name: Rune Dagger
text: After your hero attacks, gain Spell Damage +1 this turn.
flavorText: Turns out being stabbed makes you more vulnerable to magic.

name: Cagematch Custodian
text: Battlecry: Draw a weapon.
flavorText: Cleans up after a dust up.

name: Deathmatch Pavilion
text: Summon a 3/2 Duelist. If your hero attacked this turn, summon another.
flavorText: Worth it for the stuffed toy at the end.

name: Landslide
text: Deal 1 damage to all enemy minions. If you're Overloaded, deal 1 damage again.
flavorText: "And they win it by a landslide! Wait, where did all the other racers go?"

name: Flametongue Totem
text: Adjacent minions have +2 Attack.
flavorText: Totemsmiths like to use the rarest woods for their totems. There are even rumors of totems made of Ironbark Protectors.

name: Far Sight
text: Draw a card. That card costs (3) less.
flavorText: Drek'thar can't see, but he can see. You know what I mean? It's ok if you don't.

name: Feral Spirit
text: Summon two 2/3 Spirit Wolves with Taunt. Overload: (2)
flavorText: Spirit wolves are like regular wolves with pom-poms.

name: Lava Burst
text: Deal 5 damage. Overload: (2)
flavorText: It's like an ocean of liquid magma in your mouth!

name: Lightning Storm
text: Deal 2- 3 damage to all enemy minions. Overload: (2)
flavorText: An umbrella won't be effective, I'm afraid.

name: Mana Tide Totem
text: At the end of your turn, draw a card.
flavorText: It is said that some shaman can say "Floatin' totem" 10 times, fast.

name: Unbound Elemental
text: Whenever you play a card with Overload, gain +1/+1.
flavorText: Unlike bound elementals, Unbound ones really enjoy a night on the town.

name: Plague of Murlocs
text: Transform all minions into random Murlocs.
flavorText: This is horrible! And adorable!

name: Weaponized Wasp
text: Battlecry: If you control a Lackey, deal 3 damage.
flavorText: Dr. Boom had one simple request: wasps with flippin' laser beams attached to their heads.

name: Lightning Breath
text: Deal 4 damage to a minion. If you're holding a Dragon, also damage its neighbors.
flavorText: Recipe: One dragon, four wool socks, thick shag carpet.

name: Bogstrok Clacker
text: Battlecry: Transform adjacent minions into random minions that cost (1) more.
flavorText: This clacker's crackers for hacking slackers into whack attackers.

name: Lady Vashj
text: Spell Damage +1 Deathrattle: Shuffle 'Vashj Prime' into your deck.
flavorText: Personal handmaiden to Queen Azshara turned lieutenant to Illidan Stormrage. Also quite the hair sssstylist.

name: Marshspawn
text: Battlecry: If you cast a spell last turn, Discover a spell.
flavorText: Hopes to someday promote to Marshsqueen.

name: Serpentshrine Portal
text: Deal 3 damage. Summon a random 3-Cost minion. Overload: (1)
flavorText: This is why you never flush a three-cost minion.

name: Totemic Reflection
text: Give a minion +2/+2. If it's a Totem, summon a copy of it.
flavorText: "Upon reflection, I have decided that your board needs more ME."

name: Instructor Fireheart
text: Battlecry: Discover a spell that costs (1) or more. If you play it this turn, repeat this effect.
flavorText: When you have fire in your heart, even death can't stop you.

name: Molten Blast
text: Deal 2 damage. Summon that many 1/1 Elementals.
flavorText: Well, how would YOU celebrate after finals week?!

name: Grand Totem Eys'or
text: At the end of your turn, give +1/+1 to all other Totems in your hand, deck and battlefield.
flavorText: Some say it can see straight into the soul of any who dare to read its flavor text...

name: Magicfin
text: After a friendly Murloc dies, add a random Legendary minion to your hand.
flavorText: The best part is when he pulls Deathwing out of a top hat!

name: Pit Master
text: Battlecry: Summon a 3/2 Duelist. Corrupt: Summon two.
flavorText: If you win your duel, he'll throw in some of his famous Pit Master barbecue.

name: Stormstrike
text: Deal 3 damage to a minion. Give your hero +3 Attack this turn.
flavorText: When your phone is at 5%.

name: Whack-A-Gnoll Hammer
text: After your hero attacks, give a random friendly minion +1/+1.
flavorText: Hogger's most hated attraction.

name: Hex
text: Transform a minion into a 0/1 Frog with Taunt.
flavorText: If you Hex a Murloc... it really isn't much of a change, is it?

name: Windspeaker
text: Battlecry: Give a friendly minion Windfury.
flavorText: Is there anything worse than a Windspeaker with halitosis?

name: Scargil
text: Your Murlocs cost (1).
flavorText: Wanna know how he got those scars? So does he.

name: Splitting Axe
text: Battlecry: Summon copies of your Totems.
flavorText: The ancient shaman chant, "Control Axe, Control Vee."

name: Vessina
text: While you're Overloaded, your other minions have +2 Attack.
flavorText: She wasn't happy when Hagatha sent her back to Uldum. But her "angry" hiss sounds like her "happy" hiss, so no one knew the difference.

name: Squallhunter
text: Spell Damage +2 Overload: (2)
flavorText: "Oh, the weather outside is frightful… But Squallhunter's so delightful! And since we've gone down this road--overload, overload, overload!"

name: The Fist of Ra-den
text: After you cast a spell, summon a Legendary minion of that Cost. Lose 1 Durability.
flavorText: The mighty Ra-den was known as the Keeper of Storms. Unfortunately, he could not keep his fist.

name: Torrent
text: Deal 8 damage to a minion. Costs (3) less if you cast a spell last turn.
flavorText: Weeks of underwater cross-training have really built up her fourarms.

name: Vivid Spores
text: Give your minions "Deathrattle: Resummon this minion."
flavorText: Hey man, I just feel like... death is just a construct of our imaginations, ya know?

name: Dunk Tank
text: Deal 4 damage. Corrupt: Then deal 2 damage to all enemy minions.
flavorText: "When I said bring a tank to the dungeon, this is not what I had in mind!"

name: Bloodlust
text: Give your minions +3 Attack this turn.
flavorText: blaarghghLLGHRHARAAHAHHH!!

name: Doomhammer
text: Windfury, Overload: (2)
flavorText: Orgrim Doomhammer gave this legendary weapon to Thrall. His name is a total coincidence.

name: Earth Elemental
text: Taunt Overload: (3)
flavorText: Nothing beats rock.

name: Hagatha's Scheme
text: Deal 1 damage to all minions. (Upgrades each turn!)
flavorText: "All shall suffer!" "But Hagatha, those are your minions..." "I said ALL!!!"

name: Muckmorpher
text: Battlecry: Transform into a 4/4 copy of a different minion in your deck.
flavorText: Fan favorite in the muck morphin' sewer strangers.

name: Bandersmosh
text: Each turn this is in your hand, transform it into a 5/5 copy of a random Legendary minion.
flavorText: The Shudderwock finds him particularly frumious.

name: Cumulo-Maximus
text: Battlecry: If you have Overloaded Mana Crystals, deal 5 damage.
flavorText: "Are your clouds not entertained?!"

name: Dragon's Pack
text: Summon two 2/3 Spirit Wolves with Taunt. If you've Invoked twice, give them +2/+2.
flavorText: Each dragon's pack is guaranteed to have at least one rare.

name: Boggspine Knuckles
text: After your hero attacks, transform your minions into random ones that cost (1) more.
flavorText: I would NOT want to put my hand in there. It's... SQUISHY.

name: Shattered Rumbler
text: Battlecry: If you cast a spell last turn, deal 2 damage to all other minions.
flavorText: HAPPY BIRTHDAY TO THE GROUND!

name: Totem Goliath
text: Deathrattle: Summon all four basic Totems. Overload: (1)
flavorText: It was an art project, and nobody knew when to stop.

name: Inara Stormcrash
text: On your turn, your hero has +2 Attack and Windfury.
flavorText: A fan favorite, Inara is always met with thunderous applause.

name: Mistrunner
text: Battlecry: Give a friendly minion +3/+3. Overload: (1)
flavorText: "Get IT off me!!!"

name: Fire Elemental
text: Battlecry: Deal 3 damage.
flavorText: He can never take a bath. Ewww.

name: Corrupt Elementalist
text: Battlecry: Invoke Galakrond twice.
flavorText: Her element is "Horns."

name: Nithogg
text: Battlecry: Summon two 0/3 Eggs. Next turn they hatch into 4/4 Drakes with Rush.
flavorText: Not to be confused with Nithogger.

name: The Lurker Below
text: Battlecry: Deal 3 damage to an enemy minion. If it dies, repeat on one of its neighbors.
flavorText: "Throw it back! THROW IT BACK!"

name: Swampqueen Hagatha
text: Battlecry: Add a 5/5 Horror to your hand. Teach it two Shaman spells.
flavorText: Rafaam mainly enjoys working with Hagatha because she never laughs at Dr. Boom's jokes.

name: Earthquake
text: Deal 5 damage to all minions, then deal 2 damage to all minions.
flavorText: Shake it, sh-sh-sh-shake it like a Kalimdor fissure.

name: Galakrond, the Tempest
text: Battlecry: Summon two 2/2 Storms with Rush. ( )
flavorText: Hagatha cried out over the winds: "Truly, you are as powerful as the Maelstrom!" To which the Tempest answered: "I AM THE MAELSTROM."

name: Al'Akir the Windlord
text: Charge, Divine Shield, Taunt, Windfury
flavorText: He is the weakest of the four Elemental Lords. And the other three don't let him forget it.

name: Walking Fountain
text: Lifesteal, Rush, Windfury
flavorText: The weirdest part is that it doesn't have legs.

name: Tidal Wave
text: Lifesteal Deal 3 damage to all minions.
flavorText: "Hang Four, mon!"

name: Mogu Fleshshaper
text: Rush. Costs (1) less for each minion on the battlefield.
flavorText: He's here to shape *clap* you up!

name: Eye of the Storm
text: Summon three 5/6 Elementals with Taunt. Overload: (3)
flavorText: If that's the eye, I would hate to see the rest of the storm.

name: Sacrificial Pact
text: Destroy a friendly Demon. Restore 5 Health to your hero.
flavorText: This is the reason that Demons never really become friends with Warlocks.

name: Corruption
text: Choose an enemy minion. At the start of your turn, destroy it.
flavorText: It starts with stealing a pen from work, and before you know it, BOOOM! Corrupted!

name: Mortal Coil
text: Deal 1 damage to a minion. If that kills it, draw a card.
flavorText: If your spells look like horrifying skulls, let's be honest, you should get to draw some cards.

name: Soulfire
text: Deal 4 damage. Discard a random card.
flavorText: Are you lighting a soul on fire? Or burning someone with your OWN soul? This seems like an important distinction.

name: Voidwalker
text: Taunt
flavorText: No relation to "The Voidsteppers", the popular Void-based dance troupe.

name: Blood Imp
text: Stealth. At the end of your turn, give another random friendly minion +1 Health.
flavorText: Imps are content to hide and viciously taunt everyone nearby.

name: Call of the Void
text: Add a random Demon to your hand.
flavorText: "Marco!" "Polo!" "Marco!" "Who dares summon me?!"

name: Flame Imp
text: Battlecry: Deal 3 damage to your hero.
flavorText: Imps like being on fire. They just do.

name: Plague of Flames
text: Destroy all your minions. For each one, destroy a random enemy minion.
flavorText: This is fine.

name: Sinister Deal
text: Discover a Lackey.
flavorText: "So, what's in the sack?" "Something... sinister." "Okay, it's a deal."

name: Supreme Archaeology
text: Quest: Draw 20 cards. Reward: Tome of Origination.
flavorText: Archaeology is the discovery of rare and powerful artifacts. Supreme Archaeology is TAKING THEM!

name: Rain of Fire
text: Deal 1 damage to all characters.
flavorText: You know it’s autumn when the skies rain brimstone and fire. Also: pumpkin spice!

name: Fiendish Servant
text: Deathrattle: Give this minion's Attack to a random friendly minion.
flavorText: Putting the "r" in fiend.

name: Shadow Council
text: Replace your hand with random Demons. Give them +2/+2.
flavorText: Why is everybody in Outland replacing their hands?!

name: Unstable Felbolt
text: Deal 3 damage to an enemy minion and a random friendly one.
flavorText: Warning! Your minions are seated in the splash zone.

name: Demonic Studies
text: Discover a Demon. Your next one costs (1) less.
flavorText: "Do you wanna summon a demon? I wanna summon a demon!"

name: Felosophy
text: Copy the lowest Cost Demon in your hand. Outcast: Give both +1/+1.
flavorText: "Like, isn't evil subjective man?"

name: Spirit Jailer
text: Battlecry: Shuffle 2 Soul Fragments into your deck.
flavorText: "Sure, they're in your deck, but the mind is like, the REAL prison."

name: Wicked Whispers
text: Discard your lowest Cost card. Give your minions +1/+1.
flavorText: When the Old Ones whisper, others will scream.

name: Felstalker
text: Battlecry: Discard a random card.
flavorText: This puppy chews up cards instead of shoes.

name: Demonfire
text: Deal 2 damage to a minion. If it’s a friendly Demon, give it +2/+2 instead.
flavorText: Demonfire is like regular fire except for IT NEVER STOPS BURNING HELLLPPP

name: EVIL Genius
text: Battlecry: Destroy a friendly minion to add 2 random Lackeys to your hand.
flavorText: You do not want to be on the business end of this intellect!

name: Plot Twist
text: Shuffle your hand into your deck. Draw that many cards.
flavorText: It’s coming from inside the deck!

name: Expired Merchant
text: Battlecry: Discard your highest Cost card. Deathrattle: Add 2 copies of it to your hand.
flavorText: The "best by" date is more like a guideline.

name: Nether Breath
text: Deal 2 damage. If you're holding a Dragon, deal 4 damage with Lifesteal instead.
flavorText: "Whether the Nether is cold, whether the Nether is hot, we'll burn together, whatever the Nether, whether we like it or not."

name: Twisted Knowledge
text: Discover 2 Warlock cards.
flavorText: People eat eight spiders in their sleep per year. Centaurs have two rib cages. Dwarves are just counterfeit titans.

name: Darkglare
text: After your hero takes damage, refresh a Mana Crystal.
flavorText: He's got a dark glare, but he sees crystal clear!

name: Imprisoned Scrap Imp
text: Dormant for 2 turns. When this awakens, give all minions in your hand +2/+1.
flavorText: His impish imports imply impressively impetuous impropriety.

name: Kanrethad Ebonlocke
text: Your Demons cost (1) less. Deathrattle: Shuffle 'Kanrethad Prime' into your deck.
flavorText: After Illidan's downfall, Kanrethad formed the Council of the Black Harvest to study Illidan's fel magic. Some say he was... green with envy.

name: Boneweb Egg
text: Deathrattle: Summon two 2/1 Spiders. If you discard this, trigger its Deathrattle.
flavorText: Noblegarden is going to be really exciting this year!

name: Soul Shear
text: Deal 3 damage to a minion. Shuffle 2 Soul Fragments into your deck.
flavorText: "Just a little off the sides please."

name: Midway Maniac
text: Taunt
flavorText: Faire owners hate him! Learn his secrets with one simple spell!

name: Drain Life
text: Deal 2 damage. Restore 2 Health to your hero.
flavorText: "I've just sucked one year of your life away."

name: Shadow Bolt
text: Deal 4 damage to a minion.
flavorText: It’s a Bolt. It's made out of Shadow. What more do you need to know!

name: Felguard
text: Taunt Battlecry: Destroy one of your Mana Crystals.
flavorText: Yes, he'll fight for you. BUT HE'S NOT GOING TO LIKE IT.

name: Sense Demons
text: Draw 2 Demons from your deck.
flavorText: Generally demons are pretty obvious and you don’t need a spell to sense them.

name: Void Terror
text: Battlecry: Destroy both adjacent minions and gain their Attack and Health.
flavorText: If you put this into your deck, you WILL lose the trust of your other minions.

name: Impferno
text: Give your Demons +1 Attack. Deal 1 damage to all enemy minions.
flavorText: Imps don't get mad when you set them on fire. They think it's cozy.

name: Rafaam's Scheme
text: Summon 1 1/1 (Imp, Imps). (Upgrades each turn!)
flavorText: "When your first plan fails... imp-rovise."

name: EVIL Recruiter
text: Battlecry: Destroy a friendly Lackey to summon a 5/5 Demon.
flavorText: I'm starting to think the lackeys aren't evil, just taken advantage of.

name: Neferset Thrasher
text: Whenever this attacks, deal 3 damage to your hero.
flavorText: Tough to do skateboard tricks with four legs.

name: Dark Skies
text: Deal 1 damage to a random minion. Repeat for each card in your hand.
flavorText: "It's a drizzle of fire. A fine mist, really."

name: Dragonblight Cultist
text: Battlecry: Invoke Galakrond. Gain +1 Attack for each other friendly minion.
flavorText: Galakrond would be extra mad if he was resurrected with gnaw marks on his bones.

name: Chaos Gazer
text: Battlecry: Curse a playable card in your opponent's hand. They have 1 turn to play it!
flavorText: No matter the game rules, it's always playing Go Fish.

name: School Spirits
text: Deal 2 damage to all minions. Shuffle 2 Soul Fragments into your deck.
flavorText: "B-E A-G-G-R-E-S-S-I-V-E!"

name: Shadowlight Scholar
text: Battlecry: Destroy a Soul Fragment in your deck to deal 3 damage.
flavorText: Imagine having the power of soul magic and using it as a reading light.

name: Backfire
text: Draw 3 cards. Deal 3 damage to your hero.
flavorText: "That's the last time I let an imp spit gasoline into my car."

name: Free Admission
text: Draw 2 minions. If they're both Demons, reduce their Costs by (2).
flavorText: "Quick, get in before someone sees you, or worse, someone sees me."

name: Man'ari Mosher
text: Battlecry: Give a friendly Demon +3 Attack and Lifesteal this turn.
flavorText: "E.T.C. is sooo mainstream. Have you heard of Blight Boar?"

name: Revenant Rascal
text: Battlecry: Destroy a Mana Crystal for each player.
flavorText: Turns out his face really did get stuck that way.

name: Hellfire
text: Deal 3 damage to ALL characters.
flavorText: It's spells like these that make it hard for Warlocks to get decent help.

name: Pit Lord
text: Battlecry: Deal 5 damage to your hero.
flavorText: Mannoroth, Magtheridon, and Brutallus may be dead, but it turns out there are a LOT of pit lords.

name: Shadowflame
text: Destroy a friendly minion and deal its Attack damage to all enemy minions.
flavorText: Start with a powerful minion and stir in Shadowflame and you have a good time!

name: Summoning Portal
text: Your minions cost (2) less, but not less than (1).
flavorText: NOT LESS THAN 1! Don't get any ideas!

name: Eager Underling
text: Deathrattle: Give two random friendly minions +2/+2.
flavorText: Eager to please, even if it kills him.

name: Diseased Vulture
text: Whenever your hero takes damage on your turn, summon a random 3-Cost minion.
flavorText: He's off the twig! He's kicked the bucket! THIS IS AN EX-VULTURE!

name: Impbalming
text: Destroy a minion. Shuffle 3 Worthless Imps into your deck.
flavorText: With your complexion, Imp Balm is a great demonizer.

name: Fiendish Rites
text: Invoke Galakrond. Give your minions +1 Attack.
flavorText: "You have the right to sacrifice an ally. If you do not have an ally, then one will be sacrificed for you."

name: Veiled Worshipper
text: Battlecry: If you've Invoked twice, draw 3 cards.
flavorText: If you’re not wearing your regulation cultist clothing, how will Galakrond know to devour you last?

name: Nightshade Matron
text: Rush Battlecry: Discard your highest Cost card.
flavorText: Throws shade at those "high-cost" minions.

name: The Dark Portal
text: Draw a minion. If you have at least 8 cards in hand, it costs (5) less.
flavorText: Some say it's the source of Azeroth's greatest problems—aside from the gnomes.

name: Cascading Disaster
text: Destroy a random enemy minion. Corrupt: Destroy 2. Corrupt Again: Destroy 3.
flavorText: Please keep all hands, arms, feet and legs inside the ride until the monster comes to a complete stop.

name: Fire Breather
text: Battlecry: Deal 2 damage to all minions except Demons.
flavorText: "Phew! That skull has been stuck between my teeth for hours!"

name: Bane of Doom
text: Deal 2 damage to a character. If that kills it, summon a random Demon.
flavorText: My advice to you is to avoid Doom, if possible.

name: Dark Pharaoh Tekahn
text: Battlecry: For the rest of the game, your Lackeys are 4/4.
flavorText: He'll get that League of Explorers and their little murloc too!

name: Crazed Netherwing
text: Battlecry: If you're holding a Dragon, deal 3 damage to all other characters.
flavorText: Always tail swipes left.

name: Void Drinker
text: Taunt. Battlecry: Destroy a Soul Fragment in your deck to gain +3/+3.
flavorText: It has no taste.

name: Envoy Rustwix
text: Deathrattle: Shuffle 3 random Prime Legendary minions into your deck.
flavorText: "Time to roll. Rusted Legion, ho!"

name: Dread Infernal
text: Battlecry: Deal 1 damage to ALL other characters.
flavorText: "INFERNOOOOOOOOOO!" - Jaraxxus, Eredar Lord of the Burning Legion

name: Siphon Soul
text: Destroy a minion. Restore 3 Health to your hero.
flavorText: You probably should avoid siphoning your own soul. You might create some kind of weird infinite loop.

name: Aranasi Broodmother
text: Taunt When you draw this, restore 4 Health to your hero.
flavorText: She's got a big brood and a big mood.

name: Darkest Hour
text: Destroy all friendly minions. For each one, summon a random minion from your deck.
flavorText: It's always darkest just before you find the light switch.

name: Riftcleaver
text: Battlecry: Destroy a minion. Your hero takes damage equal to its Health.
flavorText: Brings you face to face with your destructive impulses.

name: Abyssal Summoner
text: Battlecry: Summon a Demon with Taunt and stats equal to your hand size.
flavorText: But gnomes have tiny hands...

name: Hand of Gul'dan
text: When you play or discard this, draw 3 cards.
flavorText: His skull also draws three cards. Imagine how many cards he could draw with HIS ENTIRE BODY!

name: Keli'dan the Breaker
text: Battlecry: Destroy a minion. If drawn this turn, instead destroy all minions except this one.
flavorText: He calms down a lot if you just give him a turn.

name: Deck of Chaos
text: Swap the Cost and Attack of all minions in your deck.
flavorText: Yeah, it's chaos, but it's organized chaos.

name: Ring Matron
text: Taunt Deathrattle: Summon two 3/2 Imps.
flavorText: But where does she keep them?

name: Tickatus
text: Battlecry: Remove the top 5 cards from your deck. Corrupt: Your opponent's deck instead.
flavorText: "These are all.... EXPIRED!"

name: Siegebreaker
text: Taunt Your other Demons have +1 Attack.
flavorText: Has a side hustle as a siegebroker.

name: Arch-Villain Rafaam
text: Taunt Battlecry: Replace your hand and deck with Legendary minions.
flavorText: Minions must wash hands before being LIQUIDATED AND REPLACED BY SOMEONE BETTER.

name: Galakrond, the Wretched
text: Battlecry: Summon 1 random Demon. ( )
flavorText: Fel-flames slowly writhed around the skeleton, until the great bones knit themselves together into a demonic monstrosity. Rafaam shielded his face from the heat but could not hide his grin.

name: Valdris Felgorge
text: Battlecry: Increase your maximum hand size to 12. Draw 4 cards.
flavorText: I don't mean to pry, but you don't by chance happen to have six fingers on both of your hands?

name: Soulciologist Malicia
text: Battlecry: For each Soul Fragment in your deck, summon a 3/3 Soul with Rush. ( )
flavorText: If you value your life, don't call it a "soft science."

name: Twisting Nether
text: Destroy all minions.
flavorText: The Twisting Nether is a formless place of magic and illusion and destroyed minions.

name: Fel Lord Betrug
text: Whenever you draw a minion, summon a copy with Rush that dies at end of turn.
flavorText: Nobody else likes rush hour.

name: Zzeraku the Warped
text: Whenever your hero takes damage, summon a 6/6 Nether Drake.
flavorText: The extra Z is for "zesty."

name: Enhanced Dreadlord
text: Taunt Deathrattle: Summon a 5/5 Dreadlord with Lifesteal.
flavorText: Photo actually taken across the street in the reflection of a doorknob.

name: Archwitch Willow
text: Battlecry: Summon a random Demon from your hand and deck.
flavorText: One of the demons will do all the work while the other gets the same grade.

name: Lord Jaraxxus
text: Battlecry: Destroy your hero and replace it with Lord Jaraxxus.
flavorText: "TRIFLING GNOME! YOUR ARROGANCE WILL BE YOUR UNDOING!!!!"

name: Jumbo Imp
text: Costs (1) less whenever a friendly Demon dies while this is in your hand.
flavorText: Jumbo in size! Huge in E.V.I.L.!

name: Inner Rage
text: Deal 1 damage to a minion and give it +2 Attack.
flavorText: They're only smiling on the outside.

name: Charge
text: Give a friendly minion Charge. It can't attack heroes this turn.
flavorText: "Guys! Guys! Slow down!" - some kind of non-warrior minion

name: Whirlwind
text: Deal 1 damage to ALL minions.
flavorText: The way to tell seasoned warriors from novice ones: the novices yell "wheeeee" while whirlwinding.

name: Shield Slam
text: Deal 1 damage to a minion for each Armor you have.
flavorText: "What is a better weapon? The sharp one your enemies expect, or the blunt one they ignore?" - The Art of Warrior, Chapter 9

name: Upgrade!
text: If you have a weapon, give it +1/+1. Otherwise equip a 1/3 weapon.
flavorText: Easily worth 50 DKP.

name: Improve Morale
text: Deal 1 damage to a minion. If it survives, add a Lackey to your hand.
flavorText: "The beatings will continue until MY morale improves."

name: Hack the System
text: Quest: Attack 5 times with your hero. Reward: Anraphet's Core.
flavorText: Anything can be hacked, if you're holding an axe.

name: Into the Fray
text: Give all Taunt minions in your hand +2/+2.
flavorText: "You are in my FRAY!"

name: Sky Raider
text: Battlecry: Add a random Pirate to your hand.
flavorText: Maybe he should've hatched a plan that could actually carry booty back too.

name: Boom Squad
text: Discover a Lackey, Mech, or Dragon.
flavorText: Discover the meaning of squad goals.

name: Risky Skipper
text: After you play a minion, deal 1 damage to all minions.
flavorText: Sworn enemy of the Safety Matey.

name: Imprisoned Gan'arg
text: Dormant for 2 turns. When this awakens, equip a 3/2 Axe.
flavorText: Factory Direct Fiery War Axe. Please allow two turns for delivery.

name: Sword and Board
text: Deal 2 damage to a minion. Gain 2 Armor.
flavorText: Stab and Slab. Charge and Targe. Slash and Bash. You get the idea.

name: Athletic Studies
text: Discover a Rush minion. Your next one costs (1) less.
flavorText: It's a quick read.

name: Spiked Wheel
text: Has +3 Attack while your hero has Armor.
flavorText: Great for driving, terrible for steering.

name: Stage Dive
text: Draw a Rush minion. Corrupt: Give it +2/+1.
flavorText: The most metal trust fall.

name: Cleave
text: Deal 2 damage to two random enemy minions.
flavorText: Hey you two…could you stand next to each other for a second…

name: Execute
text: Destroy a damaged enemy minion.
flavorText: It's okay, he deserved it.

name: Heroic Strike
text: Give your hero +4 Attack this turn.
flavorText: Really, if you're a hero, this is every strike.

name: Armorsmith
text: Whenever a friendly minion takes damage, gain 1 Armor.
flavorText: She accepts guild funds for repairs!

name: Battle Rage
text: Draw a card for each damaged friendly character.
flavorText: "You won't like me when I'm angry."

name: Commanding Shout
text: Your minions can't be reduced below 1 Health this turn. Draw a card.
flavorText: "Shout! Shout! Let it all out!" - Advice to warriors-in-training

name: Cruel Taskmaster
text: Battlecry: Deal 1 damage to a minion and give it +2 Attack.
flavorText: "I'm going to need you to come in on Sunday." - Cruel Taskmaster

name: Rampage
text: Give a damaged minion +3/+3.
flavorText: Minion get ANGRY. Minion SMASH!

name: Slam
text: Deal 2 damage to a minion. If it survives, draw a card.
flavorText: "Dun da dun, dun da dun": if you've heard an ogre sing this, it's too late.

name: Sweeping Strikes
text: Give a minion "Also damages minions next to whomever this attacks."
flavorText: Infinitely preferable to mopping strikes.

name: Vicious Scraphound
text: Whenever this minion deals damage, gain that much Armor.
flavorText: It begs for scraps.

name: Frightened Flunky
text: Taunt Battlecry: Discover a Taunt minion.
flavorText: Some people just aren't cut out to be supervillain material.

name: Ritual Chopper
text: Battlecry: Invoke Galakrond.
flavorText: Chop chop, Galakrond!

name: Corsair Cache
text: Draw a weapon. Give it +1 Durability.
flavorText: Where's a corsair's favorite place to hide treasure? Under their deck!

name: In Formation!
text: Add 2 random Taunt minions to your hand.
flavorText: None can doubt the strength of the Scholomance student body.

name: Bumper Car
text: Rush Deathrattle: Add two 1/1 Riders with Rush to your hand.
flavorText: Subject: Re: Unsafe Rides? bump

name: E.T.C., God of Metal
text: After a friendly Rush minion attacks, deal 2 damage to the enemy hero.
flavorText: There are Old Gods and then there are Rock Gods.

name: Minefield
text: Deal 5 damage randomly split among all minions.
flavorText: Dodge bombs like you're playing Tonksweeper!

name: Ringmaster's Baton
text: After your hero attacks, give a Mech, Dragon, and Pirate in your hand +1/+1.
flavorText: A mech, a dragon, and a pirate walk into an Old God's gaping maw. The mech was too crunchy, the dragon was too hot, but the pirate was just right.

name: Stage Hand
text: Battlecry: Give a random minion in your hand +1/+1.
flavorText: Holds everything himself because people wouldn't stop touching the prop table.

name: Fiery War Axe
flavorText: During times of tranquility and harmony, this weapon was called by its less popular name, Chilly Peace Axe.

name: Shield Block
text: Gain 5 Armor. Draw a card.
flavorText: Shields were invented because Face Block is USELESS.

name: Warsong Commander
text: Your Charge minions have +1 Attack.
flavorText: The Warsong clan is such drama. It's really not worth it to become a commander.

name: Frothing Berserker
text: Whenever a minion takes damage, gain +1 Attack.
flavorText: He used to work as an accountant before he tried his hand at Berserkering.

name: Clockwork Goblin
text: Battlecry: Shuffle a Bomb into your opponent's deck. When drawn, it explodes for 5 damage.
flavorText: They always wind up bombing.

name: Bloodsworn Mercenary
text: Battlecry: Choose a damaged friendly minion. Summon a copy of it.
flavorText: You look really hurt. You could use a friend!

name: Livewire Lance
text: After your Hero attacks, add a Lackey to your hand.
flavorText: The lance is heavy but it’s the battery pack that really does a number on the shoulders.

name: Ancharrr
text: After your hero attacks, draw a Pirate from your deck.
flavorText: The problem with anchors is they often end up sinking to the bottom of your deck.

name: Awaken!
text: Invoke Galakrond. Deal  1 damage to all minions.
flavorText: This is an alarm clock you can't ignore.

name: EVIL Quartermaster
text: Battlecry: Add a Lackey to your hand. Gain 3 Armor.
flavorText: He trained for a whole year to become quarter-master. Three more, and he'll be a full-master.

name: Ramming Speed
text: Force a minion to attack one of its neighbors.
flavorText: Her deductible keeps going up.

name: Skybarge
text: After you summon a Pirate, deal 2 damage to a random enemy.
flavorText: It's more of a ship-gun than a gunship.

name: Bomb Wrangler
text: Whenever this minion takes damage, summon a 1/1 Boom Bot.
flavorText: Bomb Wranglers tend to have short fuses and even shorter lifespans.

name: Bladestorm
text: Deal 1 damage to all minions. Repeat until one dies.
flavorText: Dear minions: Woosh, woosh, woosh, woosh, woosh. Best regards, Bladestorm

name: Bonechewer Raider
text: Battlecry: If there is a damaged minion, gain +1/+1 and Rush.
flavorText: And if that minion has a frisbee, LOOK OUT!

name: Bulwark of Azzinoth
text: Whenever your hero would take damage, this loses  1 Durability instead.
flavorText: This plate turned shield you shall wield, praying its powers fel will serve you well.

name: Warmaul Challenger
text: Battlecry: Choose an enemy minion. Battle it to the death!
flavorText: Old gladiator rules: first one to die loses.

name: Playmaker
text: After you play a Rush minion, summon a copy  with 1 Health remaining.
flavorText: "Here's the plan: you go left, I go right, and the wounded guy takes the hit."

name: Feat of Strength
text: Give a random Taunt minion in your hand +5/+5.
flavorText: Generally happens right after the airing of grievances.

name: Ironclad
text: Battlecry: If your hero has Armor, gain +2/+2.
flavorText: With one inch of clearance, Ironclad proved ineffective against speedbumps.

name: Kor'kron Elite
text: Charge
flavorText: The Kor'kron are the elite forces of Garrosh Hellscream. Let's just say you don't want to run into these guys while wearing a blue tabard.

name: Arathi Weaponsmith
text: Battlecry: Equip a 2/2 weapon.
flavorText: 50% off fist weapons, limited time only!

name: Mortal Strike
text: Deal 4 damage. If you have 12 or less Health, deal 6 instead.
flavorText: "If you only use one ability, use Mortal Strike." - The Warrior Code, Line 6

name: Dr. Boom's Scheme
text: Gain 1 Armor. (Upgrades each turn!)
flavorText: “We did it! We blew up the vault!” “You mean the vault door?” “Oh. The doooor…”

name: Omega Devastator
text: Battlecry: If you have 10 Mana Crystals, deal 10 damage to a minion.
flavorText: The Alpha Devastator didn’t devastate enough. The Beta Devastator devastated too much. But the Omega was just right!

name: Wrenchcalibur
text: After your hero attacks, shuffle a Bomb into your opponent's deck.
flavorText: Whoso pulleth out this wrench from the toolbox is rightwise king of the lab.

name: Restless Mummy
text: Rush Reborn
flavorText: Life-separation anxiety syndrome.

name: Molten Breath
text: Deal 5 damage to a minion. If you're holding a Dragon, gain 5 Armor.
flavorText: Pizza so hot it burns OTHER PEOPLE’S MOUTHS.

name: Scion of Ruin
text: Rush. Battlecry: If you've Invoked twice, summon 2 copies of this.
flavorText: Ruined! RUINED!

name: Kargath Bladefist
text: Rush Deathrattle: Shuffle 'Kargath Prime' into your deck.
flavorText: He rules the Shattered Hand orc clan with an iron... bladefist.

name: Reaper's Scythe
text: Spellburst: Also damages adjacent minions this turn.
flavorText: Die. Die. Die.

name: Sword Eater
text: Taunt Battlecry: Equip a 3/2 Sword.
flavorText: How tough is he? He eats swords for breakfast! Without any milk.

name: Arcanite Reaper
flavorText: No… actually you should fear the Reaper.

name: Brawl
text: Destroy all minions except one. (chosen randomly)
flavorText: Do you know the first rule of Brawl Club?

name: Plague of Wrath
text: Destroy all damaged minions.
flavorText: "Thanks, I HATE it!"

name: Scrap Golem
text: Taunt. Deathrattle: Gain Armor equal to this minion's Attack.
flavorText: Abuse, reuse, recycle.

name: Ringmaster Whatley
text: Battlecry: Draw a Mech, Dragon, and Pirate.
flavorText: His main qualification is that he'll work with anyone. Or anything.

name: Tent Trasher
text: Rush. Costs (1) less for each friendly minion with a unique minion type.
flavorText: "I consider it redecorating."

name: Armagedillo
text: Taunt At the end of your turn, give all Taunt minions in your hand +2/+2.
flavorText: We may never know what provoked it, but we will never forget the consequences.

name: Armored Goon
text: Whenever your hero attacks, gain 5 Armor.
flavorText: Armored except for non-critical areas, such as the head, torso, fists and thighs.

name: Gorehowl
text: Attacking a minion costs 1 Attack instead of 1 Durability.
flavorText: Grommash Hellscream's famous axe. Somehow this ended up in Prince Malchezaar's possession. Quite the mystery!

name: Blastmaster Boom
text: Battlecry: Summon two 1/1 Boom Bots for each Bomb in your opponent's deck.
flavorText: He's gonna fly through the air with the greatest of grease.

name: Galakrond, the Unbreakable
text: Battlecry: Draw 1 minion. Give it +4/+4. ( )
flavorText: The ground quaked beneath the behemoth as Dr. Boom continued: "…with over 400 TONS of solid Storm Silver plate." Then he beeped a small remote. "And luxury spikes!"

name: Bloodboil Brute
text: Rush Costs (1) less for each damaged minion.
flavorText: Call Gurtogg a brute if you like, but no one else cares about the wounded like he does.

name: Grommash Hellscream
text: Charge Has +6 Attack while damaged.
flavorText: Grommash drank the tainted blood of Mannoroth, dooming the orcs to green skin and red eyes! Maybe not his best decision.

name: Tomb Warden
text: Taunt Battlecry: Summon a copy of this minion.
flavorText: Also known as an ancient copy machine.

name: Deathwing, Mad Aspect
text: Battlecry: Attack ALL other minions.
flavorText: Bite that one, bite that other one, claw this one, swallow that one whole....

name: Troublemaker
text: At the end of your turn, summon two 3/3 Ruffians that attack random enemies.
flavorText: "Prepare for trouble!" "Make it double!"

name: Rattlegore
text: Deathrattle: Resummon this with -1/-1.
flavorText: He looks bad now, but he was pretty handsome in his 20/20s.

name: Dimensional Ripper
text: Summon 2 copies of a minion in your deck.
flavorText: The first dimensional ripper had a point. The second fell flat. The THIRD one really started to take shape!

name: The Boom Reaver
text: Battlecry: Summon a copy of a minion in your deck. Give it Rush.
flavorText: “What’s better than reaving? BOOM reaving!”

name: Wisp
flavorText: If you hit an Eredar Lord with enough Wisps, it will explode. But why?

name: Desk Imp
flavorText: "I feel inky!"

name: Elven Archer
text: Battlecry: Deal 1 damage.
flavorText: Don't bother asking her out on a date. She'll shoot you down.

name: Goldshire Footman
text: Taunt
flavorText: If 1/2 minions are all that is defending Goldshire, you would think it would have been overrun years ago.

name: Grimscale Oracle
text: Your other Murlocs have +1 Attack.
flavorText: These are the brainy murlocs. It turns out that doesn’t mean much.

name: Murloc Raider
flavorText: Mrrraggglhlhghghlgh, mrgaaag blarrghlgaahahl mrgggg glhalhah a bghhll graggmgmg Garrosh mglhlhlh mrghlhlhl!!

name: Stonetusk Boar
text: Charge
flavorText: This card is boaring.

name: Voodoo Doctor
text: Battlecry: Restore 2 Health.
flavorText: Voodoo is an oft-misunderstood art. But it is art.

name: Abusive Sergeant
text: Battlecry: Give a minion +2 Attack this turn.
flavorText: ADD ME TO YOUR DECK, MAGGOT!

name: Angry Chicken
text: Has +5 Attack while damaged.
flavorText: There is no beast more frightening (or ridiculous) than a fully enraged chicken.

name: Argent Squire
text: Divine Shield
flavorText: "I solemnly swear to uphold the Light, purge the world of darkness, and to eat only burritos." - The Argent Dawn Oath

name: Bloodsail Corsair
text: Battlecry: Remove 1 Durability from your opponent's weapon.
flavorText: Every pirate uses the same four digits to access Automated Gold Dispensers. It's called the "Pirate's Code".

name: Hungry Crab
text: Battlecry: Destroy a Murloc and gain +2/+2.
flavorText: Murloc. It's what's for dinner.

name: Leper Gnome
text: Deathrattle: Deal 2 damage to the enemy hero.
flavorText: He really just wants to be your friend, but the constant rejection is starting to really get to him.

name: Lightwarden
text: Whenever a character is healed, gain +2 Attack.
flavorText: She’s smaller than her sisters Mediumwarden and Heavywarden.

name: Murloc Tidecaller
text: Whenever you summon a Murloc, gain +1 Attack.
flavorText: This guy gets crazy strong at family reunions.

name: Secretkeeper
text: Whenever a Secret is played, gain +1/+1.
flavorText: Where is Mankrik’s wife? She’ll never tell.

name: Shieldbearer
text: Taunt
flavorText: Have you seen the size of the shields in this game?? This is no easy job.

name: Southsea Deckhand
text: Has Charge while you have a weapon equipped.
flavorText: Pirates are into this new fad called "Planking".

name: Worgen Infiltrator
text: Stealth
flavorText: If you want to stop a worgen from infiltrating, just yell, "No! Bad boy!"

name: Young Dragonhawk
text: Windfury
flavorText: They were the inspiration for the championship Taurenball team: The Dragonhawks.

name: Young Priestess
text: At the end of your turn, give another random friendly minion +1 Health.
flavorText: She can't wait to learn Power Word: Fortitude Rank 2.

name: Potion Vendor
text: Battlecry: Restore 2 Health to all friendly characters.
flavorText: Everyone gets two because that’s all she can hold.

name: Toxfin
text: Battlecry: Give a friendly Murloc Poisonous.
flavorText: I'm addicted to him, but I know that he's Toxfin.

name: Beaming Sidekick
text: Battlecry: Give a friendly minion +2 Health.
flavorText: Sure, I'll carry the water! And the food! And the tents! And the cursed monkey paw!

name: Jar Dealer
text: Deathrattle: Add a random 1-Cost minion to your hand.
flavorText: What's in the jar? It could be anyone!

name: Mogu Cultist
text: Battlecry: If your board is full of Mogu Cultists, sacrifice them all and summon Highkeeper Ra.
flavorText: Mogu cultists have the worst team-building exercises.

name: Murmy
text: Reborn
flavorText: Unlike other mummies, they rolled him up with rice, sliced cucumbers, and soy sauce on the side.

name: Blazing Battlemage
flavorText: Weaponized an ancient technique once used to slice cold butter.

name: Depth Charge
text: At the start of your turn, deal 5 damage to ALL minions.
flavorText: * Does not have Charge.

name: Hot Air Balloon
text: At the start of your turn, gain +1 Health.
flavorText: The Gadgetzan Pilgrim's Bounty parade is missing a float this year.

name: Ethereal Augmerchant
text: Battlecry: Deal 1 damage to a minion and give it Spell Damage +1.
flavorText: According to him, undamaged minions just spell problems.

name: Guardian Augmerchant
text: Battlecry: Deal 1 damage to a minion and give it Divine Shield.
flavorText: "What doesn't kill you makes me money!"

name: Infectious Sporeling
text: After this damages a minion, turn it into an Infectious Sporeling.
flavorText: "The best thing about being me—there’s so many 'me's."

name: Rocket Augmerchant
text: Battlecry: Deal 1 damage to a minion and give it Rush.
flavorText: "Don't worry, this won't hurt me a bit."

name: Soulbound Ashtongue
text: Whenever this minion takes damage, also deal that amount to your hero.
flavorText: He claims to be "soulbound," but I just think he's clingy.

name: Animated Broomstick
text: Rush Battlecry: Give your other minions Rush.
flavorText: "Blimey, that's a Stratocumulus 1000!"

name: Brain Freeze
text: Freeze a minion. Combo: Also deal 3 damage to it.
flavorText: "The professor called on me, and I totally froze!"

name: Devolving Missiles
text: Shoot three missiles at random enemy minions that transform them into ones that cost (1) less.
flavorText: Most intermural spell-dueling contests end with a field of wisps.

name: Intrepid Initiate
text: Spellburst: Gain +2 Attack.
flavorText: How you like them apples?

name: Pen Flinger
text: Battlecry: Deal 1 damage. Spellburst: Return this to your hand.
flavorText: The pen is also a more aerodynamic short-range projectile than the sword.

name: Primordial Studies
text: Discover a Spell Damage minion. Your next one costs (1) less.
flavorText: A long forgotten tome whose very essence seeps of magic. 40 dust, used.

name: Sphere of Sapience
text: At the start of your turn, look at your top card. You can put it on the bottom  and lose 1 Durability.
flavorText: This is what it sounds like when spheres scry.

name: Tour Guide
text: Battlecry: Your next Hero Power costs (0).
flavorText: "Here is the original blueprint for the Academy grounds! Don't mind those so-called dark chambers… They'll be at the end of the tour."

name: Wand Thief
text: Combo: Discover a Mage spell.
flavorText: "What’re ya buyin’?”

name: Armor Vendor
text: Battlecry: Give 4 Armor to each hero.
flavorText: "You look like the kind of person that would buy three sets of armor. One to wear, a spare, and a spare for the spare."

name: Guidance
text: Look at two spells. Add one to your hand or Overload: (1) to get both.
flavorText: Plainsrunning will result in disqualification.

name: Nitroboost Poison
text: Give a minion +2 Attack. Corrupt: And your weapon.
flavorText: Pouring iced milk into your vehicle's fuel tank does NOT provide a Nitro boost, but it does go great with your victory cookies.

name: Resizing Pouch
text: Discover a card with Cost equal to your remaining Mana Crystals.
flavorText: Just don't put a Resizing Pouch inside the Resizing Pouch.

name: Safety Inspector
text: Battlecry: Shuffle the  lowest-Cost card from your hand into your deck. Draw a card.
flavorText: "All right, you're good. No sign of safety anywhere."

name: Acidic Swamp Ooze
text: Battlecry: Destroy your opponent's weapon.
flavorText: Oozes love Flamenco. Don't ask.

name: Bloodfen Raptor
flavorText: "Kill 30 raptors." - Hemet Nesingwary

name: Bluegill Warrior
text: Charge
flavorText: He just wants a hug. A sloppy... slimy... hug.

name: Frostwolf Grunt
text: Taunt
flavorText: Grunting is what his father did and his father before that. It's more than just a job.

name: Kobold Geomancer
text: Spell Damage +1
flavorText: In the old days, Kobolds were the finest candle merchants in the land. Then they got pushed too far...

name: Murloc Tidehunter
text: Battlecry: Summon a 1/1 Murloc Scout.
flavorText: "Death will rise, from the tides!"

name: Novice Engineer
text: Battlecry: Draw a card.
flavorText: "Half of this class will not graduate… since they'll have been turned to chickens." - Tinkmaster Overspark, teaching Gizmos 101.

name: River Crocolisk
flavorText: Edward "Lefty" Smith tried to make luggage out of a river crocolisk once.

name: Amani Berserker
text: Has +3 Attack while damaged.
flavorText: If an Amani berserker asks "Joo lookin' at me?!", the correct response is "Nah, mon".

name: Ancient Watcher
text: Can't attack.
flavorText: Why do its eyes seem to follow you as you walk by?

name: Bloodmage Thalnos
text: Spell Damage +1 Deathrattle: Draw a card.
flavorText: He's in charge of the Annual Scarlet Monastery Blood Drive!

name: Bloodsail Raider
text: Battlecry: Gain Attack equal to the Attack of your weapon.
flavorText: "I only plunder on days that end in 'y'."

name: Crazed Alchemist
text: Battlecry: Swap the Attack and Health of a minion.
flavorText: "You'll love my new recipe!" he says... especially if you're not happy with your current number of limbs.

name: Dire Wolf Alpha
text: Adjacent minions have +1 Attack.
flavorText: We are pretty excited about the upcoming release of Dire Wolf Beta, just repost this sign for a chance at a key.

name: Doomsayer
text: At the start of your turn, destroy ALL minions.
flavorText: He's almost been right so many times. He was sure it was coming during the Cataclysm.

name: Faerie Dragon
text: Can't be targeted by spells or Hero Powers.
flavorText: Adorable. Immune to Magic. Doesn't pee on the rug. The perfect pet!

name: Knife Juggler
text: After you summon a minion, deal 1 damage to a random enemy.
flavorText: Ambitious Knife Jugglers sometimes graduate to Bomb Jugglers. They never last long enough to make it onto a card though.

name: Loot Hoarder
text: Deathrattle: Draw a card.
flavorText: Always roll need.

name: Lorewalker Cho
text: Whenever a player casts a spell, put a copy into the other player’s hand.
flavorText: Lorewalker Cho archives and shares tales from the land of Pandaria, but his favorite story is the one where Joey and Phoebe go on a road trip.

name: Mad Bomber
text: Battlecry: Deal 3 damage randomly split between all other characters.
flavorText: He's not really all that crazy, he is just not as careful with explosives as he should be.

name: Mana Addict
text: Whenever you cast a spell, gain +2 Attack this turn.
flavorText: She’s trying to kick the habit, but still takes some mana whenever she has a stressful day.

name: Mana Wraith
text: ALL minions cost (1) more.
flavorText: They come out at night to eat leftover mana crystals. "Mmmmmm," they say.

name: Master Swordsmith
text: At the end of your turn, give another random friendly minion +1 Attack.
flavorText: He's currently trying to craft a "flail-axe", but all the other swordsmiths say it can't be done.

name: Millhouse Manastorm
text: Battlecry: Enemy spells cost (0) next turn.
flavorText: "I'm gonna light you up, sweetcheeks!"

name: Nat Pagle
text: At the start of your turn, you have a 50% chance to draw an extra card.
flavorText: Nat Pagle, Azeroth's premier fisherman! He invented the Auto-Angler 3000, the Extendo-Pole 3000, and the Lure-o-matic 2099 (still in testing).

name: Pint-Sized Summoner
text: The first minion you play each turn costs (1) less.
flavorText: She's quite jealous of the Gallon-Sized Summoner.

name: Sunfury Protector
text: Battlecry: Give adjacent minions Taunt.
flavorText: She carries a shield, but only so she can give it to someone she can stand behind.

name: Wild Pyromancer
text: After you cast a spell, deal 1 damage to ALL minions.
flavorText: BOOM BABY BOOM! BAD IS GOOD! DOWN WITH GOVERNMENT!

name: Youthful Brewmaster
text: Battlecry: Return a friendly minion from the battlefield to your hand.
flavorText: His youthful enthusiasm doesn’t always equal excellence in his brews. Don’t drink the Mogu Stout!

name: Arcane Servant
flavorText: "Would sir like me to punch something?"

name: Dalaran Librarian
text: Battlecry: Silence adjacent minions.
flavorText: Don't make her raise her "shush"!

name: EVIL Cable Rat
text: Battlecry: Add a Lackey to your hand.
flavorText: Gradually driven to darkness by the promise of unobtainable cheese.

name: Hench-Clan Hogsteed
text: Rush Deathrattle: Summon a 1/1 Murloc.
flavorText: This is CLEARLY their first rodeo.

name: Mana Reservoir
text: Spell Damage +1
flavorText: If it soaks too long, it becomes a reservoir hog.

name: Spellbook Binder
text: Battlecry: If you have Spell Damage, draw a card.
flavorText: You're bound to love his work!

name: Sunreaver Spy
text: Battlecry: If you control a Secret, gain +1/+1.
flavorText: She's watching. Always watching.

name: Zayle, Shadow Cloak
text: You start the game with one of Zayle's EVIL Decks!
flavorText: E.V.I.L. is the new black.

name: Bug Collector
text: Battlecry: Summon a 1/1 Locust with Rush.
flavorText: The only one who likes BEEEES!!!

name: Dwarven Archaeologist
text: After you Discover a card, reduce its cost by (1).
flavorText: She's making great progress on paying off that advanced degree.

name: Fishflinger
text: Battlecry: Add a random Murloc to each player's hand.
flavorText: The scent of fish lingers on the fishflinger's fish fingers.

name: Injured Tol'vir
text: Taunt Battlecry: Deal 3 damage to this minion.
flavorText: Me-OW!

name: Kobold Sandtrooper
text: Deathrattle: Deal 3 damage to the enemy hero.
flavorText: Stay while, take candle.

name: Neferset Ritualist
text: Battlecry: Restore adjacent minions to full Health.
flavorText: The Neferset are great—they'll always make sure their friends are feline fine.

name: Questing Explorer
text: Battlecry: If you control a Quest, draw a card.
flavorText: Earned her merit badges the hard way—twelve zhevra hooves at a time.

name: Quicksand Elemental
text: Battlecry: Give all enemy minions -2 Attack this turn.
flavorText: Use a light abrasive to buff blemishes away but use a heavy abrasive to debuff problems.

name: Serpent Egg
text: Deathrattle: Summon a 3/4 Sea Serpent.
flavorText: These things go from "adorable danger noodle!" to "MY FACE IS MELTING!" all too quickly.

name: Spitting Camel
text: At the end of your turn,   deal 1 damage to another   random friendly minion.
flavorText: Were you expectorating another bad pun?

name: Temple Berserker
text: Reborn Has +2 Attack while damaged.
flavorText: He's back. He's angry. And he's here to wrap things up.

name: Vilefiend
text: Lifesteal
flavorText: Dreamed of becoming a Stylefiend, but fel was never in season.

name: Zephrys the Great
text: Battlecry: If your deck has no duplicates, wish for the perfect card.
flavorText: "Of course it's perfect, you're just not seeing how to use it."

name: Dragon Breeder
text: Battlecry: Choose a friendly Dragon. Add a copy of it to your hand.
flavorText: Deathwing would have been more well-adjusted if he'd been raised by this guy.

name: Evasive Chimaera
text: Poisonous Can't be targeted by spells or Hero Powers.
flavorText: One head only tells the truth, while the other head only tells lies. But they both spit poison.

name: Grizzled Wizard
text: Battlecry: Swap Hero Powers with your opponent until your next turn.
flavorText: When he was young, he was an Outrageous Magus.

name: Parachute Brigand
text: After you play a Pirate, summon this minion from your hand.
flavorText: She flies standby.

name: Tasty Flyfish
text: Deathrattle: Give a Dragon in your hand +2/+2.
flavorText: Reinforced with vitamins and mrglrls.

name: Transmogrifier
text: Whenever you draw a card, transform it into a random Legendary minion.
flavorText: All it takes is some imagination and a cardboard box.

name: Wyrmrest Purifier
text: Battlecry: Transform all Neutral cards in your deck into random cards from your class.
flavorText: She keeps your deck classy.

name: Licensed Adventurer
text: Battlecry: If you control a Quest, add a Coin to your hand.
flavorText: "Just point me in the vague direction of the things you want smashed, and you got yourself a deal!"

name: Bonechewer Brawler
text: Taunt Whenever this minion takes  damage, gain +2 Attack.
flavorText: When you get this swole, arrows are basically free acupuncture.

name: Imprisoned Vilefiend
text: Dormant for 2 turns. Rush
flavorText: If you do the time, you gotta make up the time.

name: Mo'arg Artificer
text: All minions take double damage from spells.
flavorText: Double-damage. You know the drill.

name: Rustsworn Initiate
text: Deathrattle: Summon a 1/1 Impcaster with Spell Damage +1.
flavorText: The Rusted Legion's training leaves a little to be desired. He hasn't even had a tetanus shot yet!

name: Cult Neophyte
text: Battlecry: Your opponent's spells cost (1) more next turn.
flavorText: Make a new recruit's deficiencies your efficiencies.

name: Manafeeder Panthara
text: Battlecry: If you've used your Hero Power this turn, draw a card.
flavorText: Feeds on mana, crystal kibble, and whatever it was you were just snacking on.

name: Sneaky Delinquent
text: Stealth. Deathrattle: Add a 3/1 Ghost with Stealth to your hand.
flavorText: All right, now open your lid and say "Ahh!"

name: Transfer Student
text: This has different effects based on which game board you're on.
flavorText: Oh, the places you'll go! There is so much to fight! There are boards to be explored. There are dreams to take flight.

name: Trick Totem
text: At the end of your turn, cast a random spell that costs (3) or less.
flavorText: It knows how to sit still and do tricks. Still working on rolling over, though.

name: Wandmaker
text: Battlecry: Add a 1-Cost spell from your class to your hand.
flavorText: She creates incredibly affordable wands of all shapes and sizes. But not owls. The owl is all-natural.

name: Costumed Entertainer
text: Battlecry: Give a random minion in your hand +2/+2.
flavorText: Just remember not to talk. It breaks character.

name: Crabrider
text: Rush Windfury
flavorText: "Now I'm falling asleep and she's calling a crab…"

name: Felfire Deadeye
text: Your Hero Power costs (1) less.
flavorText: She only shoots people who pet her cat without asking first.

name: Horrendous Growth
text: Corrupt: Gain +1/+1. Can be Corrupted endlessly.
flavorText: Stop picking at it! You’re only making it worse.

name: Imprisoned Phoenix
text: Dormant for 2 turns. Spell Damage +2
flavorText: It's actually pretty easy to escape chains when you can burst into flames.

name: Parade Leader
text: After you summon a Rush minion, give it +2 Attack.
flavorText: He's always going to reign on his parade.

name: Prize Vendor
text: Battlecry: Each player draws a card.
flavorText: He's just making sure they're real. Authentic tickets taste like strawberry.

name: Rock Rager
text: Taunt
flavorText: Still doesn't understand why he can't beat Paper Rager.

name: Showstopper
text: Deathrattle: Silence all minions.
flavorText: This act is killing it!

name: Wriggling Horror
text: Battlecry: Give adjacent minions +1/+1.
flavorText: Created to scare. Born to wriggle.

name: Dalaran Mage
text: Spell Damage +1
flavorText: You don't see a lot of Dalaran warriors.

name: Ironforge Rifleman
text: Battlecry: Deal 1 damage.
flavorText: "Ready! Aim! Drink!"

name: Ironfur Grizzly
text: Taunt
flavorText: "Bear Carcass 1/10"

name: Magma Rager
flavorText: He likes to think he is powerful, but pretty much anyone can solo Molten Core now.

name: Raid Leader
text: Your other minions have +1 Attack.
flavorText: "That's a 50 DKP minus!"

name: Razorfen Hunter
text: Battlecry: Summon a 1/1 Boar.
flavorText: Someone did mess with Tuskerr once. ONCE.

name: Shattered Sun Cleric
text: Battlecry: Give a friendly minion +1/+1.
flavorText: They always have a spare flask of Sunwell Energy Drink™!

name: Silverback Patriarch
text: Taunt
flavorText: He likes to act like he's in charge, but the silverback matriarch actually runs things.

name: Wolfrider
text: Charge
flavorText: Orcish raiders ride wolves because they are well adapted to harsh environments, and because they are soft and cuddly.

name: Alarm-o-Bot
text: At the start of your turn, swap this minion with a random one in your hand.
flavorText: WARNING. WARNING. WARNING.

name: Arcane Golem
text: Battlecry: Give your opponent a Mana Crystal.
flavorText: Having Arcane golems at home really classes up the place, and as a bonus they are great conversation pieces.

name: Blood Knight
text: Battlecry: All minions lose Divine Shield. Gain +3/+3 for each Shield lost.
flavorText: The Blood Knights get their holy powers from the Sunwell, which you should NOT bathe in.

name: Brightwing
text: Battlecry: Add a random Legendary minion to your hand.
flavorText: Little faerie dragons are made of sugar and spice and maniacal vice.

name: Coldlight Seer
text: Battlecry: Give your other Murlocs +2 Health.
flavorText: The Coldlight murlocs reside in the darkest pits of the Abyssal Depths. So no, there's no getting away from murlocs.

name: Demolisher
text: At the start of your turn, deal 2 damage to a random enemy.
flavorText: Laying siege isn't fun for anyone. It's not even all that effective, now that everyone has a flying mount.

name: Earthen Ring Farseer
text: Battlecry: Restore 3 Health.
